{"title_page": "Autokane", "text_new": "'''Autokane''' ({{lang-grc|\u0391\u1f50\u03c4\u03bf\u03ba\u03ac\u03bd\u03b7}}) or '''Autokana''' (\u0391\u1f50\u03c4\u03bf\u03ba\u03ac\u03bd\u03b1) was an [[Ancient Greece|ancient Greek]] city of [[Aeolis]] located on a mountain of the same name in [[Asia Minor]]. It is quoted in the third ''[[Homeric Hymn]]'' to [[Apollo]], where it is mentioned as the name of a mountain.<ref>''Homeric Hymn III'', \"To Apollo\", [https://msu.edu/~tyrrell/Apollo.htm Line 35].</ref> There was also a city with the same name through numismatic evidence consisting of coins dated to the 4th century BCE on which the inscriptions \u00ab\u0391\u03a5\u03a4\u039f\u039a\u0391\u039d\u0391\u00bb or \u00ab\u0391\u03a5\u03a4\u00bb appear.<ref name=Poleis>{{harvnb|Hansen|Nielsen|2004|loc=\"Aeolis and Soutwestern Mysia\", p. 1040}}.</ref> The site of the city is unlocated.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n*{{cite book|last1=Hansen|first1=Mogens Herman|last2=Nielsen|first2=Thomas Heine|title=An Inventory of Archaic and Classical Poleis|year=2004|location=Oxford and New York|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=0198140991|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=22jupg3FqdYC|ref=harv}}\n\n{{coord unknown|Turkey}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in ancient Aeolis]]\n[[Category:Former populated places in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Lost ancient cities and towns]]\n\n{{AncientGreece-stub}}\n{{Turkey-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Autokane''' ({{lang-grc|\u0391\u1f50\u03c4\u03bf\u03ba\u03ac\u03bd\u03b7}}) or '''Autokana''' (\u0391\u1f50\u03c4\u03bf\u03ba\u03ac\u03bd\u03b1) was an [[Ancient Greece|ancient Greek]] city of [[Aeolis]] located on a mountain of the same name in [[Asia Minor]]. It is quoted in the third ''[[Homeric Hymn]]'' to [[Apollo]], where it is mentioned as the name of a mountain.<ref>''Homeric Hymn III'', \"To Apollo\", Line 35.</ref> There was also a city with the same name through numismatic evidence consisting of coins dated to the 4th century BCE on which the inscriptions \u00ab\u0391\u03a5\u03a4\u039f\u039a\u0391\u039d\u0391\u00bb or \u00ab\u0391\u03a5\u03a4\u00bb appear.<ref name=Poleis>{{harvnb|Hansen|Nielsen|2004|loc=\"Aeolis and Soutwestern Mysia\", p. 1040}}.</ref> The site of the city is unlocated.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n*{{cite book|last1=Hansen|first1=Mogens Herman|last2=Nielsen|first2=Thomas Heine|title=An Inventory of Archaic and Classical Poleis|year=2004|location=Oxford and New York|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=0198140991|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=22jupg3FqdYC|ref=harv}}\n\n{{coord unknown|Turkey}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in ancient Aeolis]]\n[[Category:Former populated places in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Lost ancient cities and towns]]\n\n{{AncientGreece-stub}}\n{{Turkey-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Blue Branson", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Autokane"}
{"title_page": "Senegambia bridge", "text_new": "{{Infobox Bridge\n|bridge_name         = Senegambia Bridge\n|image               = SenegambiaBridge NorthApproach 23January2019.jpg\n|caption             =\n|official_name       =\n|also_known_as       = Trans-Gambia Bridge\n|carries             = [[Trans-Gambia Highway]] and [[N4 road (Senegal)|Highway N4]]\n|crosses             = [[Gambia River]]\n|locale              = [[Bamba Tenda, Gambia]] and [[Yelitenda, Gambia]]\n|maint               = National Roads Authority<ref name=nra>{{cite web |title=Trans-Gambia Corridor Project|url= http://nra.gm/service/building-constructions/ |website=National Roads Authority |accessdate=2 February 2019}}</ref>\n|id                  =\n|design              = \n|mainspan            = {{convert|100|m|yd}}\n|length              = {{convert|1.9|km|mi}}\n|width               = {{convert|12|m|feet}}\n|clearance           =\n|below               =\n|traffic             =\n|builder             = [[Isolux Cors\u00e1n]] and the [[Arezki Group]]\n|designer            = [[BCEOM]] and [[SCET Tunisie]]\n|begin               =\n|open                = January 21, 2019\n|cost                = US$ 93 million\n|closed              =\n|toll                = US$ 5 for cars\n|coordinates         = {{coord|13|30|59|N|15|34|21|W|display=inline,title}}\n}}\nThe '''Senegambia bridge''', also known as the '''Trans-Gambia Bridge''', is a bridge in [[The Gambia]] that carries the [[Trans-Gambia Highway]] connecting northern and southern Gambia. It also provides access to the isolated [[Casamance]] province from the rest of Senegal. A bridge had been proposed for this location in 1956 but political considerations delayed construction which finally began in 2015. Construction was funded largely by a loan of US$ 65 million from the [[African Development Bank]], with remaining funding coming from the Gambian government.  Construction works were carried out by a joint venture of Spanish company [[Isolux Cors\u00e1n]] and the Senegalese [[Arezki Group]].\n\nThe bridge, made from reinforced concrete, opened to light vehicles on 21 January 2019.  At {{convert|1.9|km|mi}} in length it is one of [[West Africa]]'s longest bridges and includes a {{convert|100|m|yd|adj=mid|-wide}} central span to facilitate continued use of the river by boats. The Senegambia bridge forms part of the [[Trans-Gambia Highway]] and the [[Trans\u2013West African Coastal Highway]].\n\n== Situation ==\nThe bridge lies approximately {{convert|10|km|0}} south of [[Farafenni]], a Gambian town on the border with Senegal, and carries the [[Trans-Gambia Highway]] across the [[Gambia River]].<ref name=news24>{{cite news |title=Long-awaited bridge over River Gambia inaugurated |url=https://www.news24.com/Africa/News/long-awaited-bridge-over-river-gambia-inaugurated-20190122 |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=News24 |agency=Agence France-Presse |date=22 January 2019 |language=en}}</ref> This runs east-west through The Gambia and splits the country in two. The river also prevents easy movement of people from the main portion of Senegal, which lies north of The Gambia, to its southern province of [[Casamance]] which is south of the river.<ref name=bbc>{{cite news |title=Bridge ends 'centuries' of commuting chaos |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-46973684 |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=BBC|date=23 January 2019}}</ref> Travellers had previously used a ferry crossing at this location, but it was unreliable and delays of 10\u201320 days waiting for a ferry were not uncommon.<ref name=bbc/><ref name=kemboi>{{cite news |last1=Kemboi |first1=Linus |title=Senegal inaugurates the new Senegambia bridge |url=https://constructionreviewonline.com/2019/02/senegal-inaugurates-the-new-senegambia-bridge/ |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=Construction Review Online |date=5 February 2019}}</ref> The alternative was a {{convert|400|km|mi|adj=on}} detour eastwards to the next available crossing of the Gambia River.<ref name=kemboi/>  Development in Casamance had been hindered by the poor access to the rest of the country.<ref name=news24/>\n\n== Planning ==\nThe bridge was first mooted in 1956 and the French government committed funds for its construction in 1971 but the start of works was delayed by periods of strained tensions between Gambia and Senegal.<ref name=bbc/><ref name=\"point\">{{cite news |date=23 January 2019 |title=Senegambia Bridge belongs to Gambia: President Sall |url=http://thepoint.gm/africa/gambia/article/senegambia-bridge-belongs-to-gambia-president-sall |work=The Point |access-date=23 January 2019}}</ref> The project was formerly led by the Organisation pour la Mise en Valeur du Fleuve Gambie (OMVG) which commissioned engineering feasibility studies of the scheme from French firm [[BCEOM]] and Tunisian firm [[SCET Tunisie]] in the 1990s.<ref name=nra/> These studies were updated by the same companies between 2007 and 2009 and form the basis of the current design which has a 100-year [[design life]].<ref name=nra/><ref name=apa>{{cite news |title=Landmark Senegambia bridge inaugurated |url=http://apanews.net/en/news/landmark-trans-gambia-bridge-launched |accessdate=23 February 2019 |work=Agence de Presse Africaine News |language=en}}</ref>\n\nFunding was finally secured through the African Development Fund (ADF) of the [[African Development Bank]] (ADB), which contributed US$ 65 million as lead lender for the project.<ref name=ventures>{{cite news |title=Africa is confronting border challenges with these access bridge links |url=http://venturesafrica.com/africa-is-confronting-border-pass-challenges-with-these-access-bridge-links/ |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=Ventures Africa |date=4 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Enoghase |first1=Sylvester |title=Africa Future: From Market Stall To Cyberspace |url=https://www.independent.ng/africa-future-from-market-stall-to-cyberspace/ |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=Independent Newspapers Nigeria |date=10 February 2019}}</ref> The remaining funding was approved for the project by the [[Alliance for Patriotic Reorientation and Construction]] government of Gambia; who state that no contribution was made by Senegal.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Manneh |first1=Yankuba Jallow And Nelson |title=Gambia: Review Deportation of Gambians From Abroad \u2013 APRC Interim Leader |url=https://allafrica.com/stories/201902080562.html |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=Foroyaa Newspaper |date=8 February 2019}}</ref> Approval to proceed was granted by the government of Gambia in 2011.<ref name=apa/>\n\n== Construction ==\nFinal design and planning work commenced in 2012 and construction began in 2015.<ref name=news24/><ref name=bbc/>  Construction was led by a joint-venture of Spanish company [[Isolux Cors\u00e1n]] and the Senegalese [[Arezki Group]].  The construction contract had a value of 51.7 million euros.<ref name=PR>{{cite news |title=Isolux Cors\u00e1n Awarded Its First Contract in Gambia for the Construction of a Bridge for 51.7M\u20ac |url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/isolux-corsan-awarded-its-first-contract-in-gambia-for-the-construction-of-a-bridge-for-517m-286097621.html |accessdate=23 February 2019 |work=CISION PR News Wire |language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe structure is made of reinforced concrete and has a total length of {{convert|1.9|km|mi}}&nbsp;\u2013 of which the section that crosses the river is {{convert|942|m|yd}} long.<ref name=news24/><ref name=bbc/><ref name=apa/>  It has piled foundations but unexpectedly thick layers of mud (up to {{convert|20|m|feet}} in depth) on the river banks caused delays in construction.<ref name=cr/> It is one of the longest bridges in [[West Africa]] and incorporates a {{convert|100|m|yards|adj=mid|-wide}} central span to allow for passage of boats along the river.<ref name=ventures/><ref name=PR/>  The bridge deck is {{convert|12|m|feet}} wide and carries a {{convert|7.5|m|feet|adj=mid|-wide}} single-carriageway road.<ref>{{cite web |title=From Trans-Gambia to Senegambia \u2013 A bridge over troubled water? |url=http://4ipgroup.org/trans-gambia-senegambia-bridge-troubled-water/ |website=4IP Group |accessdate=23 February 2019 |date=29 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe bridge's official name is a portmanteau of the names of Senegal and Gambia and is intended to reflect the bonds of friendship between the two countries, but it is also known as the Trans-Gambia Bridge.<ref name=cr>{{cite news |last1=Kang'ereha |first1=Dorcas |title=Gambia to inaugurate Trans-Gambia Bridge in January 2019 |url=https://constructionreviewonline.com/2018/07/gambia-to-inaugurate-trans-gambia-bridge-in-january-2019/ |accessdate=25 February 2019 |work=Construction Review Online |date=26 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=inaug/>  Total project costs were $93 million.<ref name=apa/> A large portion of the workforce were local: 58 % were Gambians and 20 % were from the wider [[ECOWAS]] countries.<ref name=cr/>\n\nThe bridge's opening ceremony took place on 21 January 2019 and was led by Gambia's President Adama Barrow and Senegal's President Macky Sall who made the first official crossing of the bridge together shortly after 4:30&nbsp;p.m. local time.<ref name=bbc/><ref>{{cite news |title=S\u00e9n\u00e9gal \u2013 Gambie: inauguration du \u00ab Senegambia Bridge \u00bb (vid\u00e9o de r\u00e9alisation) |url=https://beninwebtv.com/2019/01/senegal-gambie-inauguration-du-senegambia-bridge-video-de-realisation/ |accessdate=23 February 2019 |work=Benin Web TV |date=23 January 2019 |language=fr-FR}}</ref> Gambian Vice President [[Fatoumata Tambajang]], the minister of works [[Bai Lamin Jobe]] and his Senegalese counterpart [[Abdoulaye Daouda Diallo]] were also in attendance.<ref name=inaug>{{cite news |title=Senegambia Bridge Inaugurated |url=http://foroyaa.gm/senegambia-bridge-inaugurated/ |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=Foroyaa Newspaper |date=22 January 2019}}</ref><ref name=koaci/> Zinguinchor mayor Abdoulaye Bald\u00e9 and Senegalese national football team coach [[Aliou Ciss\u00e9]] were also present and Senegalese musician [[Youssou Ndour]] performed music at the opening ceremony.<ref name=bbc/><ref name=koaci>{{cite news |title=S\u00e9n\u00e9gal-Gambie : Macky Sall et Adama Barrow inaugurent le \u00ab Senegambia Bridge \u00bb |url=https://www.koaci.com/senegal-gambie-macky-sall-adama-barrow-inaugurent-senegambia-bridge--127145.html |accessdate=23 February 2019 |work=KOACI}}</ref>  \n\nWork to complete the bridge is ongoing, which prevents its opening to anything heavier than a small car.<ref>{{cite news |title=Why Is The Senegambia Bridge Opened Before Completion? |url=http://foroyaa.gm/why-is-the-senegambia-bridge-opened-before-completion/ |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=Foroyaa Newspaper |date=24 January 2019}}</ref>  A toll of US$5 is levied for each crossing.<ref name=bbc/> Completion of the structure is expected in July 2019.<ref name=bbc/>  The bridge forms part of a link on the proposed [[Trans\u2013West African Coastal Highway]], part of the [[Trans-African Highway network]].<ref name=nra/> This project, spearheaded by the [[New Partnership for Africa's Development]] seeks to link [[Nouakchott]] in Mauritania with [[Lagos]] in [[Nigeria]] via a 15-country, {{convert|4560|km|mi|adj=on}} highway in the hope of boosting trade and co-operation in the region.<ref>{{cite web |title=Highways link 15 West African countries |url=https://www.un.org/africarenewal/magazine/october-2006/highways-link-15-west-african-countries |website=United Nations |publisher=Africa Renewal Online}}</ref>\n\n== Post-construction ==\nIt is hoped that the road will improve co-operation between Gambia and Senegal and facilitate trade in minerals, fuels and foodstuffs.<ref name=ventures/><ref name=inaug/> It has had a marked effect on journey times; a trip by road from [[Dakar]] to [[Ziguinchor]] which previously took a day can now be completed within five hours.<ref name=bbc/> Local ferry operators and roadside vendors have complained about the loss of revenue following construction of the bridge.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jabkhiro |first1=Juliette |title=Trans-Gambia bridge a boon for trade, but a blow for local traders |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-gambia-senegal-bridge/trans-gambia-bridge-a-boon-for-trade-but-a-blow-for-local-traders-idUKKCN1PP202 |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=Reuters |date=1 February 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nThere is a dispute between the Gambia Ferries Service and the National Roads Authority over which government agency is entitled to the revenue from the bridge. The [[Ministry of Works, Transport and Infrastructure]] has negotiated a temporary arrangement whereby the revenue is split between the two. The Gambian press has criticised the government for failing to set up a [[public\u2013private partnership]] to ensure tolls fund the future maintenance of the structure.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Mbai |first1=Pa Nderry |title=The Trans-Gambia Bridge \u2013 A Symbol of Senegambian Unity or A Source of Discord |url=https://www.freedomnewspaper.com/2019/02/14/the-trans-gambia-bridge-a-symbol-of-senegambian-unity-or-a-source-of-discord/ |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=Freedom Newspaper |date=15 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:SenegambiaBridge HeavyVehicleFerry 23January2019.jpg|The vehicle ferry to be replaced by the completed bridge\nFile:Senegambia Bridge Peak Southward View.jpg|View to the south from the bridge peak, towards [[Soma, Gambia|Soma]]\nFile:Senegambia Bridge Peak Northward View.jpg|View to the north from the bridge peak, towards [[Farafenni]]\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Bridges completed in 2019]]\n[[Category:Bridges in Gambia]]\n[[Category:Road bridges]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Bridge\n|bridge_name= Senegambia Bridge\n|image=SenegambiaBridge NorthApproach 23January2019.jpg\n|caption=\n|official_name=\n|also_known_as= Trans-Gambia Bridge\n|carries= [[Trans-Gambia Highway]] and [[N4 road (Senegal)|Highway N4]]\n|crosses= [[Gambia River]]\n|locale= [[Bamba Tenda, Gambia]] and [[Yelitenda, Gambia]]\n|maint= National Roads Authority<ref name=nra>{{cite web |title=Trans-Gambia Corridor Project\n|url=http://nra.gm/service/building-constructions/ |website=National Roads Authority |accessdate=2 February 2019}}</ref>\n|id=\n|design= \n|mainspan={{convert|100|m|yd}}\n|length={{convert|1.9|km|mi}}\n|width={{convert|12|m|feet}}\n|clearance=\n|below =\n|traffic=\n|builder =  [[Isolux Cors\u00e1n]] and the [[Arezki Group]]\n|designer= [[BCEOM]] and [[SCET Tunisie]]\n|begin=\n|open= January 21, 2019\n|cost=$93 million\n|closed=\n|toll                = US$ 5 for cars\n|coordinates = {{coord|13|30|59|N|15|34|21|W|display=inline,title}}\n}}\nThe '''Senegambia bridge''', also known as the '''Trans-Gambia Bridge''', is a bridge in [[The Gambia]] that carries the [[Trans-Gambia Highway]] connecting northern and southern Gambia. It also provides access to the isolated [[Casamance]] province from the rest of Senegal. A bridge had been proposed for this location in 1956 but political considerations delayed construction which finally began in 2015. Construction was funded largely by a loan of US$ 65 million from the [[African Development Bank]], with remaining funding coming from the Gambian government.  Construction works were carried out by a joint venture of Spanish company [[Isolux Cors\u00e1n]] and the Senegalese [[Arezki Group]].\n\nThe bridge, made from reinforced concrete, opened to light vehicles on 21 January 2019.  At {{convert|1.9|km|mi}} in length it is one of [[West Africa]]'s longest bridges and includes a {{convert|100|m|yd|adj=mid|-wide}} central span to facilitate continued use of the river by boats. The Senegambia bridge forms part of the [[Trans-Gambia Highway]] and the [[Trans\u2013West African Coastal Highway]].\n\n== Situation ==\nThe bridge lies approximately {{convert|10|km|0}} south of [[Farafenni]], a Gambian town on the border with Senegal, and carries the [[Trans-Gambia Highway]] across the [[Gambia River]].<ref name=news24>{{cite news |title=Long-awaited bridge over River Gambia inaugurated |url=https://www.news24.com/Africa/News/long-awaited-bridge-over-river-gambia-inaugurated-20190122 |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=News24 |agency=Agence France-Presse |date=22 January 2019 |language=en}}</ref> This runs east-west through The Gambia and splits the country in two. The river also prevents easy movement of people from the main portion of Senegal, which lies north of The Gambia, to its southern province of [[Casamance]] which is south of the river.<ref name=bbc>{{cite news |title=Bridge ends 'centuries' of commuting chaos |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-46973684 |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=BBC|date=23 January 2019}}</ref> Travellers had previously used a ferry crossing at this location, but it was unreliable and delays of 10\u201320 days waiting for a ferry were not uncommon.<ref name=bbc/><ref name=kemboi>{{cite news |last1=Kemboi |first1=Linus |title=Senegal inaugurates the new Senegambia bridge |url=https://constructionreviewonline.com/2019/02/senegal-inaugurates-the-new-senegambia-bridge/ |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=Construction Review Online |date=5 February 2019}}</ref> The alternative was a {{convert|400|km|mi|adj=on}} detour eastwards to the next available crossing of the Gambia River.<ref name=kemboi/>  Development in Casamance had been hindered by the poor access to the rest of the country.<ref name=news24/>\n\n== Planning ==\nThe bridge was first mooted in 1956 and the French government committed funds for its construction in 1971 but the start of works was delayed by periods of strained tensions between Gambia and Senegal.<ref name=bbc/><ref name=\"point\">{{cite news |date=23 January 2019 |title=Senegambia Bridge belongs to Gambia: President Sall |url=http://thepoint.gm/africa/gambia/article/senegambia-bridge-belongs-to-gambia-president-sall |work=The Point |access-date=23 January 2019}}</ref> The project was formerly led by the Organisation pour la Mise en Valeur du Fleuve Gambie (OMVG) which commissioned engineering feasibility studies of the scheme from French firm [[BCEOM]] and Tunisian firm [[SCET Tunisie]] in the 1990s.<ref name=nra/> These studies were updated by the same companies between 2007 and 2009 and form the basis of the current design which has a 100-year [[design life]].<ref name=nra/><ref name=apa>{{cite news |title=Landmark Senegambia bridge inaugurated |url=http://apanews.net/en/news/landmark-trans-gambia-bridge-launched |accessdate=23 February 2019 |work=Agence de Presse Africaine News |language=en}}</ref>\n\nFunding was finally secured through the African Development Fund (ADF) of the [[African Development Bank]] (ADB), which contributed US$ 65 million as lead lender for the project.<ref name=ventures>{{cite news |title=Africa is confronting border challenges with these access bridge links |url=http://venturesafrica.com/africa-is-confronting-border-pass-challenges-with-these-access-bridge-links/ |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=Ventures Africa |date=4 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Enoghase |first1=Sylvester |title=Africa Future: From Market Stall To Cyberspace |url=https://www.independent.ng/africa-future-from-market-stall-to-cyberspace/ |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=Independent Newspapers Nigeria |date=10 February 2019}}</ref> The remaining funding was approved for the project by the [[Alliance for Patriotic Reorientation and Construction]] government of Gambia; who state that no contribution was made by Senegal.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Manneh |first1=Yankuba Jallow And Nelson |title=Gambia: Review Deportation of Gambians From Abroad \u2013 APRC Interim Leader |url=https://allafrica.com/stories/201902080562.html |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=Foroyaa Newspaper |date=8 February 2019}}</ref> Approval to proceed was granted by the government of Gambia in 2011.<ref name=apa/>\n\n== Construction ==\nFinal design and planning work commenced in 2012 and construction began in 2015.<ref name=news24/><ref name=bbc/>  Construction was led by a joint-venture of Spanish company [[Isolux Cors\u00e1n]] and the Senegalese [[Arezki Group]].  The construction contract had a value of 51.7 million euros.<ref name=PR>{{cite news |title=Isolux Cors\u00e1n Awarded Its First Contract in Gambia for the Construction of a Bridge for 51.7M\u20ac |url=https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/isolux-corsan-awarded-its-first-contract-in-gambia-for-the-construction-of-a-bridge-for-517m-286097621.html |accessdate=23 February 2019 |work=CISION PR News Wire |language=en}}</ref>\n\nThe structure is made of reinforced concrete and has a total length of {{convert|1.9|km|mi}}&nbsp;\u2013 of which the section that crosses the river is {{convert|942|m|yd}} long.<ref name=news24/><ref name=bbc/><ref name=apa/>  It has piled foundations but unexpectedly thick layers of mud (up to {{convert|20|m|feet}} in depth) on the river banks caused delays in construction.<ref name=cr/> It is one of the longest bridges in [[West Africa]] and incorporates a {{convert|100|m|yards|adj=mid|-wide}} central span to allow for passage of boats along the river.<ref name=ventures/><ref name=PR/>  The bridge deck is {{convert|12|m|feet}} wide and carries a {{convert|7.5|m|feet|adj=mid|-wide}} single-carriageway road.<ref>{{cite web |title=From Trans-Gambia to Senegambia \u2013 A bridge over troubled water? |url=http://4ipgroup.org/trans-gambia-senegambia-bridge-troubled-water/ |website=4IP Group |accessdate=23 February 2019 |date=29 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe bridge's official name is a portmanteau of the names of Senegal and Gambia and is intended to reflect the bonds of friendship between the two countries, but it is also known as the Trans-Gambia Bridge.<ref name=cr>{{cite news |last1=Kang'ereha |first1=Dorcas |title=Gambia to inaugurate Trans-Gambia Bridge in January 2019 |url=https://constructionreviewonline.com/2018/07/gambia-to-inaugurate-trans-gambia-bridge-in-january-2019/ |accessdate=25 February 2019 |work=Construction Review Online |date=26 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=inaug/>  Total project costs were $93 million.<ref name=apa/> A large portion of the workforce were local: 58 % were Gambians and 20 % were from the wider [[ECOWAS]] countries.<ref name=cr/>\n\nThe bridge's opening ceremony took place on 21 January 2019 and was led by Gambia's President Adama Barrow and Senegal's President Macky Sall who made the first official crossing of the bridge together shortly after 4:30&nbsp;p.m. local time.<ref name=bbc/><ref>{{cite news |title=S\u00e9n\u00e9gal \u2013 Gambie: inauguration du \u00ab Senegambia Bridge \u00bb (vid\u00e9o de r\u00e9alisation) |url=https://beninwebtv.com/2019/01/senegal-gambie-inauguration-du-senegambia-bridge-video-de-realisation/ |accessdate=23 February 2019 |work=Benin Web TV |date=23 January 2019 |language=fr-FR}}</ref> Gambian Vice President [[Fatoumata Tambajang]], the minister of works [[Bai Lamin Jobe]] and his Senegalese counterpart [[Abdoulaye Daouda Diallo]] were also in attendance.<ref name=inaug>{{cite news |title=Senegambia Bridge Inaugurated |url=http://foroyaa.gm/senegambia-bridge-inaugurated/ |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=Foroyaa Newspaper |date=22 January 2019}}</ref><ref name=koaci/> Zinguinchor mayor Abdoulaye Bald\u00e9 and Senegalese national football team coach [[Aliou Ciss\u00e9]] were also present and Senegalese musician [[Youssou Ndour]] performed music at the opening ceremony.<ref name=bbc/><ref name=koaci>{{cite news |title=S\u00e9n\u00e9gal-Gambie : Macky Sall et Adama Barrow inaugurent le \u00ab Senegambia Bridge \u00bb |url=https://www.koaci.com/senegal-gambie-macky-sall-adama-barrow-inaugurent-senegambia-bridge--127145.html |accessdate=23 February 2019 |work=KOACI}}</ref>  \n\nWork to complete the bridge is ongoing, which prevents its opening to anything heavier than a small car.<ref>{{cite news |title=Why Is The Senegambia Bridge Opened Before Completion? |url=http://foroyaa.gm/why-is-the-senegambia-bridge-opened-before-completion/ |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=Foroyaa Newspaper |date=24 January 2019}}</ref>  A toll of US$5 is levied for each crossing.<ref name=bbc/> Completion of the structure is expected in July 2019.<ref name=bbc/>  The bridge forms part of a link on the proposed [[Trans\u2013West African Coastal Highway]], part of the [[Trans-African Highway network]].<ref name=nra/> This project, spearheaded by the [[New Partnership for Africa's Development]] seeks to link [[Nouakchott]] in Mauritania with [[Lagos]] in [[Nigeria]] via a 15-country, {{convert|4560|km|mi|adj=on}} highway in the hope of boosting trade and co-operation in the region.<ref>{{cite web |title=Highways link 15 West African countries |url=https://www.un.org/africarenewal/magazine/october-2006/highways-link-15-west-african-countries |website=United Nations |publisher=Africa Renewal Online}}</ref>\n\n== Post-construction ==\nIt is hoped that the road will improve co-operation between Gambia and Senegal and facilitate trade in minerals, fuels and foodstuffs.<ref name=ventures/><ref name=inaug/> It has had a marked effect on journey times; a trip by road from [[Dakar]] to [[Ziguinchor]] which previously took a day can now be completed within five hours.<ref name=bbc/> Local ferry operators and roadside vendors have complained about the loss of revenue following construction of the bridge.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jabkhiro |first1=Juliette |title=Trans-Gambia bridge a boon for trade, but a blow for local traders |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-gambia-senegal-bridge/trans-gambia-bridge-a-boon-for-trade-but-a-blow-for-local-traders-idUKKCN1PP202 |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=Reuters |date=1 February 2019 |language=en}}</ref>\n\nThere is a dispute between the Gambia Ferries Service and the National Roads Authority over which government agency is entitled to the revenue from the bridge. The [[Ministry of Works, Transport and Infrastructure]] has negotiated a temporary arrangement whereby the revenue is split between the two. The Gambian press has criticised the government for failing to set up a [[public\u2013private partnership]] to ensure tolls fund the future maintenance of the structure.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Mbai |first1=Pa Nderry |title=The Trans-Gambia Bridge \u2013 A Symbol of Senegambian Unity or A Source of Discord |url=https://www.freedomnewspaper.com/2019/02/14/the-trans-gambia-bridge-a-symbol-of-senegambian-unity-or-a-source-of-discord/ |accessdate=22 February 2019 |work=Freedom Newspaper |date=15 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery>\nFile:SenegambiaBridge HeavyVehicleFerry 23January2019.jpg|The vehicle ferry to be replaced by the completed bridge\nFile:Senegambia Bridge Peak Southward View.jpg|View to the south from the bridge peak, towards [[Soma, Gambia|Soma]]\nFile:Senegambia Bridge Peak Northward View.jpg|View to the north from the bridge peak, towards [[Farafenni]]\n</gallery>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Bridges completed in 2019]]\n[[Category:Bridges in Gambia]]\n[[Category:Road bridges]]\n", "name_user": "Aguacatala", "label": "safe", "comment": "Update", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Senegambia_bridge"}
{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Mexico", "text_new": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Mexico}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use American English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Current disaster|event=disease pandemic|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Mexico\n| map1            = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Mexico.svg\n| legend1         = Map of the outbreak in Mexico (as of April 11)\n{{legend|#FCEED3|Confirmed 1~10}}\n{{legend|#F2A88D|Confirmed 11~50}}\n{{legend|#E36654|Confirmed 51~100}}\n{{legend|#E5354B|Confirmed 101~250}}\n{{legend|#87353F|Confirmed 251~500}}\n{{legend|#630606|Confirmed 501~1,000}}\n{{legend|#450404|Confirmed 1,001~5,000}}\n| map2            = \n| legend2         = \n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Mexico]]\n| first_case      = [[Mexico City]] and [[Los Mochis]]<ref name=\"First\" />\n| arrival_date    = 28 February 2020<br>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=02|day1=28|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], China<br /> (via Italy and the United States)<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.informador.mx/mexico/Confirman-siete-casos-de-coronavirus-en-Mexico-20200307-0085.html |title= Confirman siete casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico |language=Spanish |work=informador.mx |date=7 March 2020 |access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n| recovery_cases  = 634 <small>(as of April 2, 2020)</small><ref name=\"youtube1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=urlavWn2FWw&feature=youtu.be&t=675 |title=#ConferenciaDePrensa: #Coronavirus #COVID19 #Qu\u00e9dateEnCasaYa &#124; 1\u00b0 de abril de 2020 |publisher=YouTube |date= |accessdate=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n| deaths          = 273\n| confirmed_cases = 4219\n| suspected_cases = 9,983\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{URL|https://coronavirus.gob.mx/}}\n}}\nThe [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached [[Mexico]] in February 2020. As of April 11, there had been 4219 cases of COVID-19 in Mexico and 273 reported deaths.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/salud/casos-confirmados-de-covid-19-suben-a-4-219-se-registran-273-muertes |title= CASOS CONFIRMADOS DE COVID-19 SUBEN A 4,219; SE REGISTRAN 273 MUERTES |author= Redacci\u00f3n |date= April 11, 2020 |language=es |website= El Financiero}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Mexico medical cases chart}}\n\n=== January 2020 ===\nOn 22 January 2020, the [[Secretariat of Health (Mexico)|Secretariat of Health]] issued a statement saying that the novel coronavirus COVID-19 did not present a danger to Mexico. 441 cases have been confirmed in [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic in mainland China|China]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Thailand|Thailand]], [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in South Korea|South Korea]], and [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|the United States]], and a travel advisory was issued on 9 January.<ref name=indigo />\n\nOn January 30, 2020 before the declaration of a pandemic by the [[World Health Organization]] the Government of Mexico designed a ''Preparation and Response Plan'' that was made by the National Committee for Health Safety, a working group led by Secretariat of Health composed by different health entities aiming to act upon the imminent arrival of the pandemic. This group carried out a series of alert measures, rehabilitation and updating of epidemiological regulations based on the International Health Regulations, being the first Latam country that deployed a [[mathematical modelling of infectious disease]].<ref name=salud />\n\n=== February 2020 ===\nThe cruise ship ''[[Grand Princess]]'' docked in [[Puerto Vallarta]] (15 February), [[Manzanillo, Colima|Manzanillo]] (16 February), [[Mazatl\u00e1n]] (17 February) and [[Cabo San Lucas]](18 February), spending 9 to 12 hours in each port. The first COVID-19 death in California was a man who had been on this ship on an earlier cruise. This ship was later quarantined off San Francisco and docked in Oakland 11 March with 21 onboard who tested positive for the coronavirus.<ref>[https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2020-03-09/what-we-know-about-grand-princess-docking-coronavirus-quarantine What we know about Grand Princess docking] Los Angeles Times</ref>\n\nThe cruise ship {{ship||MSC Meraviglia}}, which was not allowed to dock in the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Cayman Islands|Cayman Islands]] or [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Jamaica|Jamaica]], docked in [[Cozumel]], Quintana Roo, on 27 February. Three passengers were diagnosed with ''[[influenza A virus]],'' but no cases of coronavirus were found.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://politica.expansion.mx/mexico/2020/02/26/el-crucero-que-arribo-a-cozumel-esta-libre-de-coronavirus |title=El crucero que arrib\u00f3 a Cozumel est\u00e1 libre de coronavirus |trans-title=The cruise ship that arrived in Cozumel is free of coronaviruses |language=es |work=Expansi\u00f3n Politica |date=27 February 2020 |access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 February, Mexico confirmed its first three cases. A 35-year-old man and a 59-year-old man in [[Mexico City]] and a 41-year-old man in the northern state of [[Sinaloa]] tested positive and were held in isolation at a hospital and a hotel, respectively. They had travelled to [[Bergamo]] and stayed in Italy for a week in mid-February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://losangeles.cbslocal.com/2020/02/28/mexico-confirms-its-first-2-coronavirus-cases/|title=Mexico Confirms Its First 2 Coronavirus Cases|last=|first=|date=28 February 2020|website=CBS Los Angeles |url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.trust.org/item/20200228134645-auoh9/|title=Mexico confirms first coronavirus cases in two men returned from Italy|last=Foundation|first=Thomson Reuters|website=news.trust.org|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"First\">{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/GobiernoMX/status/1233418133353844736|title=La @SSalud_mx confirm\u00f3 dos casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico, el primero en la capital y el segundo en Sinaloa. Se trata de pacientes de bajo riesgo que est\u00e1n siendo atendidos. Invitamos a la poblaci\u00f3n a seguir informada y tomar medidas de prevenci\u00f3n|last=M\u00e9xico|first=Gobierno de|date=28 February 2020|website=@GobiernoMX|language=es|access-date=28 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://elfinanciero.com.mx/salud/van-3-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-en-mexico|title=Van 3 casos confirmados de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico|website=El Financiero|language=es|access-date=29 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 February, a fourth case was detected and confirmed in the city of [[Torre\u00f3n]], in the state of [[Coahuila]], from a 20-year-old woman who traveled to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.milenio.com/estados/coronavirus-torreon-confirma-miguel-riquelme-caso-covid19|title=Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: lo \u00faltimo del nuevo caso en Torre\u00f3n|website=www.milenio.com|accessdate=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== March 2020 ===\n====March 1 to 15====\nOn 1 March, a fifth case was announced in [[Chiapas]] in a student who had just returned from Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnoticias.mx/confirman-caso-de-coronavirus-en-chiapas/159656|title=Confirman caso de coronavirus en Chiapas|website=ABC Noticias|language=es|date=1 March 2020|accessdate=1 March 2020}}</ref> On 6 March, a sixth case was confirmed in the [[State of Mexico]] in a 71-year-old man who had returned from Italy on 21 February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://politica.expansion.mx/mexico/2020/03/06/confirman-sexto-caso-de-coronavirus-en-el-estado-de-mexico|title=La Secretar\u00eda de Salud confirma el sexto caso de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico|date=7 March 2020|website=ADNPol\u00edtico|accessdate=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nCOVID-19 was the topic of conversation at the meeting of the National Governors' Conference (Conago) held on 5 March 2020. In addition to governors from different states (or state health representatives), the directors of [[Instituto de Salud para el Bienestar|Instituto de Salud para el Bienestar (INSABI)]], [[Mexican Social Security Institute|IMSS]], and [[Institute for Social Security and Services for State Workers|ISSSTE]] participated.<ref name=conago>[https://www.elsoldecuernavaca.com.mx/local/analizan-gobernadores-situacion-del-coronavirus-4928720.html Governors analyze the situation of Coronavirus] {{in lang|es}} by Miriam Estrada, ''El Sol de Cuernavaca'', 5 Mar 2020, retrieved 16 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nOn March 6 during the first session of National Council of Health, [[Hugo L\u00f3pez-Gatell Ram\u00edrez]], one of the main strategists and spokespersons of Mexican Government on pandemics, led the first daily press conference on Covid-19.<ref name=nat_coun_health>{{Citation|title=Conferencia de prensa. Informe diario sobre coronavirus COVID-19 en M\u00e9xico. Secretar\u00eda de Salud|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZruOELSa7vA|language=en|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n\nOn 7 March, a seventh case was also confirmed in [[Mexico City]] in a 46-year-old male who had previously had contact with another confirmed case in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reporteindigo.com/reporte/confirman-el-septimo-caso-de-coronavirus-en-mexico/|title=Se eleva a 7 el n\u00famero de casos confirmados de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico|accessdate=9 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 March, an eighth case was reported in [[Puebla (state)|Puebla]], a 47-year-old German man who had returned from a business trip to Italy.<ref name=\"8 cases\">{{cite web |first1=|title=Puebla reporta primer caso positivo de coronavirus |url=https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/nacional/proveedor-aleman-de-volkswagen-dio-positivo-a-coronavirus-secretaria-de-salud-de-puebla |website=El Financiero |publisher=Cuartoscuro |accessdate=11 March 2020}}</ref> On the same date, 40 members of a dance company in Puebla, returning from a tour in Italy, were quarantined.<ref name=\"Ballet Ce Acatl\">{{cite web |last1=Arellano Garc\u00eda |first1=Cesar |title=Supervisar\u00e1n salud de ballet folkl\u00f3rico que vuelve de Italia |url=https://www.jornada.com.mx/ultimas/politica/2020/03/10/supervisaran-salud-de-ballet-folklorico-que-vuelve-de-italia-4751.html |website=La Jornada |publisher=La Jornada |accessdate=11 March 2020|date=10 March 2020 }}</ref> The [[Mexican Stock Exchange]] fell to a record low on 10 March due to fears of the coronavirus and because of falling oil prices. The [[Bank of Mexico|Bank of Mexico (Banxico)]] stepped in to prop up the value of the peso, which fell 14% to 22.929 per US dollar.<ref name=banixco>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/mexicos-stock-market-hits-record-low-over-coronavirus-crisis-and-collapsing-oil-prices Mexico's stock market hits record low over coronavirus crisis and collapsing oil prices] {{in lang|en}} ''El Universal'' (English), 10 March 2020</ref>\n\nOn 11 March, a ninth case was confirmed in the city of [[Monterrey]], [[Nuevo Le\u00f3n]]. A 57-year-old man, who had recently come back from a trip all across Europe, was placed under quarantine. The man, who has remained anonymous, came back from his trip a week before and had contact with eight other people who have also been placed under quarantine in their houses. The man has been confirmed to reside in the city of [[San Pedro Garza Garc\u00eda]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mty.telediario.mx/local/confirman-el-primer-caso-de-coronavirus-en-nuevo-leon|title=Confirman el primer caso de coronavirus en Nuevo Le\u00f3n|date=11 March 2020|website=Telediario Monterrey|language=es|access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 March, Mexico announced it had a total of 15 confirmed cases, with new cases in [[Puebla]] and [[Durango]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.msn.com/es-mx/noticias/mexico/ya-son-15-casos-de-coronavirus-en-m%C3%A9xico-hay-82-sospechosos/ar-BB117yPi?ocid=msedgntp|title=Ya son 15 casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; hay 82 sospechosos|website=www.msn.com|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> A day later, senator {{ill|Samuel Garc\u00eda Sep\u00falveda|es}} accused the federal government of hiding the true number of confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sdpnoticias.com/local/nuevo-leon/gobierno-de-mexico-esconde-cifras-coronavirus-pandemia-samuel-garcia.html |title=Gobierno de M\u00e9xico ESCONDE cifras reales de CORONAVIRUS, acusa Samuel Garc\u00eda|last=SDPnoticias.com|website=SDPnoticias.com |language=spanish|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> After that, the government of Nuevo Le\u00f3n declared Phase 2. Mexico on 13 March had confirmed a total of 16 cases.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}}\n\nOn 13 March, it was confirmed that the [[Mexican Stock Exchange]] Chairman, [[Jaime Ruiz Sacristan]], tested positive as an asymptomatic case.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://elfinanciero.com.mx/salud/da-positivo-de-coronavirus-el-presidente-de-la-bolsa-mexicana-jaime-ruiz-sacristan|title=Da positivo de coronavirus el presidente de la Bolsa Mexicana, Jaime Ruiz Sacrist\u00e1n|website=El Financiero|language=es|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> Later, the Secretariat of Health announced in press conference that the number of confirmed cases had risen to 26.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Espino |first1=Manuel |title=M\u00e9xico suma 26 casos positivos de coronavirus |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-13-de-marzo-mexico-suma-26-casos-positivos-de-coronavirus |website=El Universal |date=14 March 2020 |publisher=El Universal, compa\u00f1\u00eda period\u00edstica Nacional |accessdate=14 March 2020 |ref=13 March 26 cases}}</ref> Several universities, including the [[National Autonomous University of Mexico|UNAM]] and [[Monterrey Institute of Technology and Higher Education|Tec de Monterrey]], switched to virtual classes. Authorities announced to be considering the cancellation of the ''Festival Internacional de Cine de Guadalajara''. In M\u00e9rida, the ''Tianguis Tur\u00edstico'' was postponed to September. Several major sporting events were also canceled.<ref name=cancelations>{{cite web |url=https://www.informador.mx/mexico/Suspenden-actividades-masivas-por-coronavirus-20200313-0020.html |title=Suspenden actividades masivas por coronavirus |trans-title=Massive Suspension of Activities Due to Coronavirus |language=Spanish |work=Informador.mx |date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Jos\u00e9 Alfonso Su\u00e1rez del Real y Aguilera entregando gel antibacterial.jpg|thumb|On 14 March 2020 sport events such as female football matches were open to public. At Estadio Ol\u00edmpico Universitario, authorities were pouring hand sanitizer at the entrance.]]\nOn 14 March, [[Fernando Petersen]], the secretary of health of the state of [[Jalisco]], confirmed the first two cases of COVID-19 were detected in Hospital Civil de [[Guadalajara]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.informador.mx/jalisco/Confirman-primeros-dos-casos-de-coronavirus-en-Jalisco-20200314-0052.html|title=Confirman primeros dos casos de coronavirus en Jalisco|website=El Informador: Noticias de Jalisco, M\u00e9xico, Deportes & Entretenimiento|language=es-ES|access-date=14 March 2020}}</ref> Two new cases were confirmed in Nuevo Le\u00f3n, and the [[Secretariat of Public Education (Mexico)|Secretariat of Public Education (SEP)]] announced that all sporting and civic events in schools would be canceled.<ref name=sep>{{cite web |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-sep-cancela-eventos-deportivos-y-civicos-en-escuelas |title=SEP cancela eventos deportivos y c\u00edvicos en escuelas por coronavirus |trans-title=SEP cancels sporting and civic events in schools due to coronavirus |language=Spanish |work=El Universal |date=14 March 2020}}</ref> The same day, the Secretariat of Education announced that Easter break, originally planned from 6 to 17 April, would be extended from 20 March to 20 April as a preventive measure.<ref name=\"Prevention Easter break in schools\">{{cite web |last1=Huizache |first1=Dolores |title=SEP anuncia que vacaciones de Semana Santa se adelantan por coronavirus |url=https://www.am.com.mx/noticias/SEP-anuncia-que-vacaciones-de-Semana-Santa-se-adelantan-por-coronavirus-20200314-0021.html |website=AM Mexico |publisher=EDITORIAL MARTINICA S.A. DE C.V. |accessdate=14 March 2020}}</ref> The [[Secretariat of Finance and Public Credit|Secretariat of Finance and Public Credit (SCHP)]] announced it was taking measures to prevent a 0.5% fall in [[Gross domestic product |gross domestic product (GDP)]].<ref name=schp>{{cite web |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/cartera/listo-paquete-contraciclico-para-impulsar-economia |title=Por Covid-19, Hacienda tiene plan contrac\u00edclico |trans-title=Because of coronavirus, Treasury has a countercyclical package ready to boost economy |work=El Universal |date=14 March 2020 |access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref> Drugstores in [[Cuernavaca]] report shortages of masks, antibacterial gel, and other items.<ref>[https://www.elsoldecuernavaca.com.mx/local/comienzan-a-escasear-productos-por-covid-19-4971890.html Products start to be scarce due to COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} Jessica Arellano, ''El Sol de Cuernavaca'', 14 Mar 2020</ref> On the same day the [[Universidad Aut\u00f3noma de Nuevo Le\u00f3n|Autonomous University of Nuevo Leon, (UANL)]] (the country's third largest university in terms of student population) suspended classes for its more than 206,000 students starting on March 17 and ending on April 20.<ref name=uanl>{{cite web |last1=Garza|first1=Aracely|title= Universidad Aut\u00f3noma de NL suspende clases por Covid-19|language=es|trans-title=Autonomous University of NL suspends classes because of Covid-19|url= https://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/universidad-autonoma-de-nl-suspende-clases-por-covid-19/1369792 |website=Exc\u00e9lsior |date=14 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Garza|first1=Aracely|language=es|title= Suspende UANL clases virtuales |url= https://m.imagenradio.com.mx/suspende-uanl-clases-virtuales |website=Imagen Radio |date=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nBusinessman Jos\u00e9 Kuri was reported in critical condition on 14 March after a trip to [[Vail, Colorado]], United States, although early reports of his death were false.<ref>{{cite web|website=El Sol de M\u00e9xico|title=El empresario Jos\u00e9 Kuri se encuentra en estado cr\u00edtico a causa de coronavirus|trans-title=The businessman Jos\u00e9 Kuri is in critical condition due to coronavirus|language=es|date=15 Mar 2020|accessdate=16 Mar 2020|author=EFE|url=https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/mexico/sociedad/el-empresario-jose-kuri-se-encuentra-en-estado-critico-a-causa-de-coronavirus-4974999.html}}</ref> As of 14 March, there have been 41 confirmed cases of [[COVID-19]] in Mexico.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://politica.expansion.mx/presidencia/2020/03/14/mexico-llega-a-41-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-con-155-sospechosos |title=M\u00e9xico llega a 41 casos confirmados de coronavirus, con 155 casos sospechosos |work=expansion.mx |language=Spanish |date=14 March 2020 |access-date=16 March 2020|trans-title=Mexico has 41 confirmed and 155 suspected cases of coronavirus}}</ref>\n\nThe 14 and 15 March ''Festival Vive Latino'' (rock and Latin music) in Mexico City opened according to schedule, in spite of fears of contagion. Temperatures of the 70,000 people who attend each day were taken at the door and anti-bacterial gel was widely distributed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/14/el-coronavirus-avanza-apresurado-en-mexico-y-las-pruebas-de-detencion-cuestan-hasta-18000-pesos/ |title=El coronavirus avanza apresurado en M\u00e9xico y las pruebas de detecci\u00f3n cuestan hasta 18,000 pesos |trans-title=Coronavirus rushes ahead in Mexico and screening tests cost up to 18,000 pesos |language=Spanish |work=Infobae |date=14 March 2020 |access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref> Organizers said that the ''[[Passion Play of Iztapalapa]]'' would continue as scheduled in Holy Week. Tito Dom\u00ednguez, vice president of the organizing committee, noted that a miracle had saved Iztapalapa during the [[Cholera outbreaks and pandemics|cholera outbreak in 1833]].<ref>[https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/metropoli/cdmx/pasion-de-cristo-en-iztapalapa-podria-cancelarse-debido-al-covid-19-coronavirus-claudia-sheinbaum-iglesia-catolica-pasion-de-cristo-coronavirus-covid-19-mexico-4974131.html Coronavirus will not stop the Stations of the Cross in Iztapalapa: organizing committee] {{in lang|es}} Maleny Navarro, ''El Sol de M\u00e9xico''. 15 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nOn 15 March, Head of Government [[Claudia Sheinbaum]] stated that Mexico City expects to spend an extra MXN $100 million (US$4.4 million) to prevent the spread of COVID-19.<ref name=sheinbaum>[https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/metropoli/cdmx/preven-gasto-de-100-mdp-extra-para-combatir-coronavirus-en-cdmx-4974203.html Expenditure of 100 extra mp to prevent coronavirus in CDMX] {{in lang|es}} by Maleny Navarro, ''El Sol de M\u00e9xico'', 15 Mar 2020</ref> The first confirmed case of coronavirus in [[Acapulco]], Guerrero, was reported.<ref>[https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/republica/sociedad/confirman-primer-caso-de-covid-19-en-guerrero-coronavirus-4974870.html Confirman primer caso de Covid-19 en Guerrero] {{in lang|es}} by Jos\u00e9 Francisco Zorroza, ''El Sol de Acapulco'', 15 Mar 2020</ref> [[Quer\u00e9taro]] reported two new cases, bringing the total to six.<ref>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/mundo/coronavirus-covid-19/nota/1932576/0/aumenta-seis-el-numero-de-casos-de-coronavirus-en-queretaro#info Queretaro increases the number of coronavirus cases to six] {{in lang|es}} by Francisco Floes Hernndez, El Universal, 15 Mar 2020</ref> [[Nuevo Leon]] reported its fifth case.<ref>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/estados/coronavirus-suman-5-casos-positivos-en-nuevo-leon Coronavirus: 5 positive cases in Nuevo Leon] {{in lang|es}} by David Carrizales, 15 Mar 2020</ref> The [[Norte\u00f1o (music)|Norte\u00f1o]] group Los Tres Tristes Tigres released a [[corrido|song]] on 15 March titled \"El corrido del coronavirus\".<ref>[https://www.elsoldecuernavaca.com.mx/doble-via/virales/video-el-pin-coronavirus-a-todos-saco-de-quicio-el-nuevo-corrido-de-los-los-tres-tristes-tigres-covid19-covid-19-salud-humor-canciones-musica-nortea-comparas-de-panico-papel-de-bano-tom-hanks-amlo-disneyland-viral-corrido-4974778.html Los Tres Tristes Tigres compose \"El corrido del coronavirus\"] {{in lang|es}} by Miguel Ceballos, ''El Sol de Puebla'', 15 Mar 2020</ref>\n\n====March 16 to 22====\n[[File: Panic buying in mexico due to covid19.jpg |thumbnail|right|Panic buying of toilet paper at a [[Soriana]] supermarket in [[Ensenada, Baja California]] due to the COVID-19 pandemic.]]\nAs of 16 March, President L\u00f3pez Obrador continued to downplay the impact of coronavirus. \"Pandemics ... won't do anything to us,\" and accused the press and the opposition for its reportage.<ref>[https://www.latimes.com/world-nation/story/2020-03-19/as-mexican-peso-collapses-over-coronavirus-threat-criticism-falls-on-president-lopez-obrador \"As Mexican peso collapses over coronavirus threat, criticism falls on president Lopez Obrador\" Los Angeles Times 2020/03/20] accessed 20 March 2020</ref>  On 16 March, lawyer Marco Antonio del Toro petitioned the federal courts to cease all but essential activities for a period of 30 to 40 days because of the coronavirus outbreak.<ref>[https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/mexico/piden-suspender-actividades-en-juzgados-y-tribunales-por-coronavirus-covid-19-mexico-contagios-pandemia-epidemia-4976721.html Suspension of judicial activities for coronavirus requested] {{in lang|es}} Manrique Gandaria, ''El Sol de M\u00e9xico'', 16 Mar 2020</ref> The total of confirmed cases reached 82.<ref name=\"Marc 16 confirmed cases\">{{cite web |last1=Castillo Torres |first1=Gustavo |title=Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: 82 casos confirmados; s\u00f3lo 2% est\u00e1n graves |url=https://www.unotv.com/noticias/portal/nacional/detalle/coronavirus-mexico-82-casos-confirmados-solo-2-estan-graves-785052/ |website=UnoTV |date=17 March 2020 |publisher=AMX Contenido S.A. de C.V. |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> The [[Universidad Aut\u00f3noma del Estado de Morelos|Autonomous University of the State of Morelos, (UAEM)]] suspended classes for its 22,000 students.<ref name=uaem>[https://www.milenio.com/estados/uaem-suspende-clases-por-coronavirus UAEM suspends classes due to coronavirus] {{in lang|es}} by David Monroy, ''Milenio'', 16 Mar 2020</ref> A diplomatic incident arose between the governments of Mexico and [[El Salvador]], concerning 12 Salvadorean citizens wearing face masks on a plane departing from Mexico City to San Salvador. [[Nayib Bukele]], president of El Salvador denounced as \"irresponsible\" that they were allowed to board the plane along with other passengers and offered to send a plane to transport them without contact with other people. The claim was supported by [[Avianca]] airline<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/AviancaCAM/status/1239696214469337088|title=Agradecemos al Presidente del El Salvador @nayibbukele por darnos la informaci\u00f3n y alertarnos sobre los pacientes con COVID-19 intentando abordar el vuelo de Avianca #431 proveniente de la Ciudad de M\u00e9xico hacia El Salvador el d\u00eda 16 de Marzo de 2020.|last=Centroam\u00e9rica|first=Avianca|date=2020-03-16|website=@AviancaCAM|language=es|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> while the Mexican government said that there were no reasons to assume that they were positive for COVID-19. Eventually, the flight was cancelled. [[Marcelo Ebrard]], head of Foreign Affairs announced after negative results of COVID tests of that Salvadorean passengers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.milenio.com/politica/coronavirus-llama-ebrard-nayib-bukele-aclarar-fuentes-pasajeros|title=Coronavirus: llama Ebrard a Nayib Bukele aclarar fuentes de pasajeros|website=www.milenio.com|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref>\n\nOn 17 March, 11 new cases were confirmed, raising the national total to 93, with [[Campeche]] being the only state with no confirmed cases.<ref name=\"Confirmed cases 17 March\">{{cite web |last1=Milenio Digital |title=Secretar\u00eda de Salud reporta 93 casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; hay 206 sospechosos |url=https://www.milenio.com/politica/coronavirus-mexico-93-casos-confirmados-206-sospechosos |website=Milenio.com |publisher=Milenio Diario, S.A de C.V |accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref> Mexico's limited response, including allowing a large concert and the women's soccer championship, as well as a lack of testing, have been criticized. Critics note that president [[Andr\u00e9s Manuel L\u00f3pez Obrador|L\u00f3pez Obrador]] does not practice social distancing but continues to greet large crowds, and the borders have not been closed. Of particular concern is the health of thousands of migrants in temporary camps along the border with the United States. The former national commissioner for influenza in Mexico during the [[2009 flu pandemic]], Alejandro Mac\u00edas, said the problem is compounded by the fact that Mexico lacks sufficient intensive care unit beds, medical care workers and ventilators.<ref>[https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/mexico-government-pressure-coronavirus-response-200316210710906.html Mexico's government under pressure over coronavirus response] by Jihan Abdalla, Al Jazeera, 17 March 2020  [https://thehill.com/latino/488100-mexico-under-international-criticism-for-coronavirus-response Mexico under international criticism for coronavirus response] BY RAFAEL BERNAL, The Hill, 18 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nOn 18 March, 25 more cases were confirmed raising the total to 118 cases and 314 suspected cases.<ref name=\"18march\">{{cite web |url=https://heraldodemexico.com.mx/pais/coronavirus-mexico-casos-confirmados-positivos-covid19-hoy-miercoles-18-marzo-secretaria-salud/|title= Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: Hay 118 casos confirmados de COVID-19|date=March 18, 2020|language=es|work=El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.milenio.com/politica/coronavirus-mexico-118-casos-confirmados-314-sospechosos |title= Confirman 118 casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; hay 314 sospechosos |date=March 18, 2020|language=es|work=Milenio}}</ref> Authorities in Jalisco are concerned about a group of 400 people who recently returned from [[Vail, Colorado]]; 40 people have symptoms of COVID-19.<ref>[https://www.milenio.com/internacional/coronavirus-mexico-18-marzo-noticias-hora-casos-vivo Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico, noticias de \u00faltima hora] Milenio, 18 Mar 2020</ref><ref>[https://www.latimes.com/world-nation/story/2020-03-20/some-of-mexicos-wealthiest-residents-went-to-colorado-to-ski-they-brought-home-coronavirus \"Some of Mexico's Wealthiest Residents Went to Colorado to Ski and Brought Home Coronavirus\". Los Angeles Times 2020/03/20] accessed 20 March 2020.</ref> The same day, the Mexican government announced that they will allocate 3.5 billion pesos ({{abbr|approx.|approximately}} 146 million US dollars{{refn|on March 18}}) to buy medical and laboratory equipment, washing and disinfection material, and ventilators.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-18-de-marzo-aumentan-118-los-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-en-mexico |title= AUMENTAN A 118 LOS CASOS CONFIRMADOS DE CORONAVIRUS EN M\u00c9XICO |date=March 18, 2020|language=es|work=El Universal}}</ref> During the night  the first COVID-19 related death in the country was confirmed, a 41-year-old man without a travel history outside the country who was hospitalized at the National Institute of Respiratory Diseases (INER).<ref name=\"death1\">{{cite web|url= https://www.jornada.com.mx/ultimas/politica/2020/03/18/fallece-victima-de-covid-19-en-el-iner-9638.html |title= Fallece primera v\u00edctima de Covid-19 en el INER |date=March 18, 2020|language=es|work=[[La Jornada]]}}</ref> Colima Governor [[Jos\u00e9 Ignacio Peralta]] declared a state of emergency after the state's first case, a man who had recently returned from Germany, was reported on 17 March.<ref>[https://www.informador.mx/mexico/Colima-declara-emergencia-por-COVID-19-20200318-0134.html Colima declara emergencia por COVID-19] El Informador, 18 Mar 2020</ref> [[Ford Motor Company|Ford]], [[Honda]], and [[Audi]] closed their manufacturing plants in Mexico.<ref name=ford>{{cite news|author=<!-- not stated -->|title=Empresas automotrices suspenden producci\u00f3n en M\u00e9xico|language=es |url=https://www.informador.mx/economia/Empresas-automotrices-suspenden-produccion-en-Mexico-20200318-0114.html|website=El Informador|date=March 18, 2020|access-date=March 19, 2020}}</ref> Hundreds of hotel employees in [[Canc\u00fan]] were fired.<ref name=cancun>[https://laverdadnoticias.com/quintanaroo/Coronavirus-Cancun-Comenzaron-los-despidos-en-los-hoteles-20200318-0006.html Coronavirus Canc\u00fan: Comenzaron los despidos en los hoteles] {{in lang|es}} by Angel Bal\u00e1n, La Verdad, 18 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nAuthorities announced on 18 March that they were looking for hundreds of citizens who may be carriers of the coronavirus, especially in the states of Puebla, Jalisco, Aguascalientes, and Guerrero. A four-member family in Puebla who had traveled to the United States kept their symptoms secret as they visited neighbors in La Vista and visited a gym. Authorities were still trying to track down the 400 people in Jalisco and Nayarit who recently traveled to Vail, Colorado. In Aguascalientes they were looking to track down passengers of Fight 2638 who traveled with a sick man from New York. The [[Autonomous University of Guerrero|Autonomous University of Guerrero (UAGRO)]] in Chilpancingo closed after a female student tested positive for the virus. The Technical Institute of Guerrero and the state Supreme Court also closed.<ref name=look>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/mexican-authorities-are-tracking-hundreds-possible-covid-19-carriers Mexican authorities are tracking hundreds of possible Covid 19 carriers] {{in lang|en}} by David Carrizales, 19 Mar 2020</ref>\n\n[[Morelos]] had its first two confirmed cases on 19 March\u2014a 54-year-old woman from [[Cuautla, Morelos|Cuautla]] and a 37-year-old man from [[Cuernavaca]].<ref>[https://www.diariodemorelos.com/noticias/urgente-confirmados-ya-2-casos-de-coronavirus-en-morelos URGENTE: CONFIRMADOS YA 2 CASOS DE CORONAVIRUS COVID19 EN MORELOS] {{in lang|es}} ''Diario de Morelos'', 19 Mar 2020</ref> [[Sinaloa]] announced its third case, a 20-year-old woman from [[Culiac\u00e1n]].<ref>[https://www.debate.com.mx/culiacan/Confirman-el-tercer-caso-de-coronavirus-en-Sinaloa-20200319-0157.html Confirman el tercer caso de coronavirus en Sinaloa] {{in lang|es}} by FRANCISCO CASTRO, ''Debate'', 19 Mar 2020</ref>\n\nU.S Secretary of State [[Mike Pompeo]] announced on 20 March there would be restrictions on travel across the [[Mexico\u2013United States border]]. Said restrictions would not apply to cargo.<ref name=pompeo>{{cite web|website=Deadline|title=President Donald Trump Goes Off On NBC News Reporter, Comcast During Coronavirus Press Briefing|date=March 20, 2020|author=Ted Johnson|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/u-s-and-mexico-to-restrict-non-essential-travel-on-southern-border-mike-pompeo-warns-of-disinformation-1202888618/|language=en}}</ref> The [[Instituto Nacional de Antropolog\u00eda e Historia|National Institute of Anthropology and History (INAH)]] announced that the archaeological zones [[Teotihuac\u00e1n]], [[Xochicalco]], and [[El Tepozteco]] will be closed on 21\u201322 March. [[Chich\u00e9n Itz\u00e1]] will close indefinitely starting 21 March. [[Guachimontones]] will close 21, 22, and 23 March. [[Palenque]], [[Tula (Mesoamerican site)|Tula]] and [[Tingambato]] will close 21 March.<ref name=inah>[https://launion.com.mx/morelos/zona-sur/noticias/157226-cerraran-las-zonas-arqueologicas-de-xochicalco-y-tepoztlan.html?utm_medium=Social&utm_source=Facebook&fbclid=IwAR3J791dkyCGjqbxVpYJPQhZ2i6AJi6PvA9ylt65t0LS1hN20dxAET1jjoA#Echobox=1584718003 Cerrar\u00e1n las zonas arqueol\u00f3gicas de Xochicalco y Tepoztl\u00e1n] {{in lang|es}} La Union de Morelos, 20 Mar 2020</ref> [[Alsea (company)|Alsea]], which operates restaurants such as Starbucks, VIPS, and Domino's Pizza offered its employees unpaid leave.<ref name=alsea>[https://www.diariodemorelos.com/noticias/starbucks-y-vips-ofrecen-empleados-dejar-de-trabajar-un-mes-sin-goce-de-sueldo-por-covid-19?fbclid=IwAR1bHSJdt5O5D8QECH-3Yk547e2nKDlW-eZtwO870EFtZHBUAlkQOjOjr4s Starbucks y VIPs ofrecen a empleados dejar de trabajar un mes sin goce de sueldo, por COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} El Diario de Morelos, 20 Mar 2020</ref> Mayor Juanita Romero (PAN) of [[Nacozari de Garc\u00eda Municipality]], Sonora, declares a curfew, in effect until 20 April. Only the [[President of Mexico]] has the legal authority to declare such a declaration.<ref name=curfew>[https://www.proceso.com.mx/622668/nacozari-toque-de-queda Alcaldesa de Nacozari ordena toque de queda, facultad exclusiva del presidente] {{in lang|es}} by Milton Martinez, Proceso, 20 Mar 2020</ref> During the night, 38 more cases and one more death were confirmed raising the total to 203 cases, 2 deaths, and 606 suspected cases.<ref name=\"20march\">{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/seguridad/coronavirus-20-de-marzo-mexico-confirma-dos-muertos-por-covid-19-suma-203-casos |title= M\u00c9XICO CONFIRMA DOS MUERTOS POR CORONAVIRUS; SUMA 203 CASOS POSITIVOS |date=March 20, 2020|language=es|work=El Universal |author1= Alexis Ortiz |author2= Perla Miranda }}</ref>\n\nOn March 21 the total confirmed cases were 251.<ref name=\"21march\">{{cite web |url= https://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/sube-a-251-el-numero-de-contagiados-de-coronavirus-en-mexico/1371282 |title= Sube a 251 el n\u00famero de contagiados de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico |date=March 21, 2020|language=es|work=Exc\u00e9lsior |author1= Redacci\u00f3n}}</ref> One day later 65 more cases were confirmed and the total of suspected cases grew to 793.<ref name=\"22march\">{{cite web |url= https://www.eleconomista.com.mx/politica/Cifra-de-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-en-Mexico-sube-a-316-Secretaria-de-Salud-20200322-0050.html |title= Con 316 casos confirmados, sigue fase de transici\u00f3n |date=March 22, 2020|language=es|work=El Economista |author1= Rolando Ramos}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 March, bars, nightclubs, movie theaters, and museums were closed in Mexico City.<ref name=bars>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/mexico-city-closes-museums-bars-nightclubs-and-movie-theaters-bid-halt-coronavirus-spread Mexico City closes museums, bars, nightclubs, and movie theaters in a bid to halt coronavirus spread] {{in lang|en}} El Universal, 23 March 2020</ref> Governor [[Enrique Alfaro Ram\u00edrez]] of Jalisco announced that beginning Thursday, 26 March, Jalisco and seven other states in the [[Baj\u00edo]] and western Mexico will block flights from areas such as [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in California|California]] that have a high rate of coronavirus. He also said that they will purchase 25,000 testing kits.<ref name=planes>[https://www.debate.com.mx/guadalajara/Jalisco-bloquearia-vuelos-y-compra-25-mil-pruebas-de-COVID-19-20200323-0224.html Jalisco will block flights and buy 25 thousand tests of COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} by CAROLINA SOL\u00cdS, Debate, 23 March</ref>\n\n====March 23 to 31====\n[[File:Acceso de personas con s\u00edntomas de enfermedades respiratorias al Instituto Nacional de Ciencias M\u00e9dicas y Nutrici\u00f3n Salvador Zubir\u00e1n.jpg|thumbnail|right|People entering to a specially respiratory illness symptom assessment area at the [[Salvador Zubir\u00e1n National Institute of Health Sciences and Nutrition|Instituto Nacional de Ciencias M\u00e9dicas y Nutrici\u00f3n Salvador Zubir\u00e1n]], Mexico City, Mexico. The hospital was converted into a special care area for COVID patients.]]\n\nMexico entered Phase 2 of the coronavirus pandemic on 23 March 2020, according to the [[World Health Organization]], with 367 confirmed cases. Phase 2 includes cases where the sick individuals did not have direct contact with someone who had recently been in another country.<ref name=who>{{cite web |url= https://www.forbes.com.mx/noticias-salud-mexico-fase-2-pandemia-por-coronavirus-oms/ |title= M\u00e9xico, en Fase 2 de pandemia por Coronavirus: OMS |language=es |date= March 23, 2020 |website= Forbes M\u00e9xico}}</ref> On the same day it was confirmed that two more people died from COVID-19, raising the total to 4 reported deaths.<ref name=\"23march\">{{cite web |url= https://www.sdpnoticias.com/nacional/muertos-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-en-mexico-cifras-23-de-marzo.html |title= Suman 4 muertos por Covid-19 en M\u00e9xico; confirman 367 casos de contagio |date=March 23, 2020|language=es|work=SDP Noticias |author1= Alexis Pav\u00f3n}}</ref> That day was announced on President L\u00f3pez Obrador's daily press conference the realization of the National Campaign of Healthy Distancing ({{ill|Jornada Nacional de Sana Distancia|lt=|es||WD=}}) a national program of non-pharmaceutical measures based on [[social distancing]] among the behavioral changes suggested by WHO as hand washing, covering one's mouth when coughing, maintaining distance from other people, and monitoring and [[self-isolation]] for people who suspect they are infected.<ref name=social>{{cite web |url=https://www.jornada.com.mx/ultimas/politica/2020/03/23/comienza-la-jornada-nacional-de-sana-distancia-1056.html|title=Comienza la Jornada Nacional de Sana Distancia|last=L|first=Ang\u00e9lica Enciso|date=2020-03-23|work=[[La Jornada]]|language=es|access-date=2020-03-27}}</ref> On that same day in the daily press conference was announced also a media campaign led by \"Susana Distancia\" (wordplay of a healthy distance) a fictional female [[superhero]] aiming to promote social distancing into the people.<ref name=susana>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dw.com/en/mexican-superhero-susana-distancia-swoops-in-to-promote-social-distancing/a-52873960|title=Mexican superhero Susana Distancia swoops in to promote social distancing|last=Martyr|first=Kate|work=[[Deutsche Welle]]|language=en-GB|date=21 March 2020|access-date=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nMeanwhile, a [[Warren Mitofsky|Mitofsky poll]] showed that 63% of Mexicans feared contracting Covid-19 and 25.5% feared dying from it. 28% said they were not willing to stay in their homes. 38.6% believed President L\u00f3pez Obrador was handling the situation well, and 37% disapproved.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/23/coronavirus-en-mexico-crece-el-descontento-con-el-gobierno-de-amlo-y-el-temor-al-contagio/ |title= Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: crece el descontento con el gobierno de AMLO y el temor al contagio |language=es |date= March 23, 2020 |website= Infobae}}</ref> Access to supermarkets in [[Coahuila]] was limited to one person per family, and the temperature of that person was taken before entering. The same rule applies to drugstores and convenience stores in the state, which has 12 confirmed cases of Covid-19.<ref name=supermarket>{{cite web |url= https://mvsnoticias.com/noticias/estados/solo-una-persona-por-familia-podra-acceder-a-supermercados-en-coahuila/ |title= Solo una persona por familia podr\u00e1 acceder a supermercados en Coahuila |author= Notimex  |language=es |date= March 23, 2020 |website= MVS Noticias}}</ref>\n\nAt his morning news conference on 24 March, President [[Andr\u00e9s Manuel L\u00f3pez Obrador|L\u00f3pez Obrador]] announced that Mexico entered Phase 2 of the coronavirus pandemic, in effect until April 30. Gatherings of more than 100 people are prohibited, and both the army and the navy will participate. The armed forces have 1,738 doctors, 1,727 nurses, 100 intensive therapy ambulances, and 400 ambulances for transportation. The military also has 5 high specialty hospitals, 36 second-level hospitals, and 272 first-level hospitals with 262 health brigades across the country. 4 deaths, 367 confirmed cases, and 826 suspected cases of COVID-19 have been reported.<ref name=amlo_phase2>{{cite web |url= https://www.unotv.com/noticias/portal/nacional/detalle/coronavirus-en-mexico-amlo-anuncia-plan-de-proteccion-contra-covid-19-776166/ |title= M\u00e9xico inicia fase 2 por coronavirus; toma estas medidas |author=  |language=es |date= March 24, 2020 |website= UNO TV}}</ref> The first Mexican woman died from COVID-19 on March 24, raising the total to 5 reported deaths in the country.<ref name=\"death5\">{{cite web|url= https://www.radioformula.com.mx/noticias/mexico/20200324/5-muertos-por-coronavirus-covid-19-mexico-martha-mujer-hospital-angeles-hoy/| title= Muere la primera mujer por Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; van 5 decesos|author=Diego Santiago|work=Grupo F\u00f3rmula|date= March 24, 2020}}</ref> On the same day 405 total cases of COVID-19 were confirmed.<ref name=\"24march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/nacional/suman-5-decesos-por-coronavirus-en-mexico-suben-a-405-los-casos-confirmados/|title= Suman 5 decesos por coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; suben a 405 los casos confirmados |author= Redacci\u00f3n |work=El Financiero|date= March 24, 2020|language=es}}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March, Dr. Abelardo \u00c1vila, researcher at the [[Salvador Zubir\u00e1n National Institute of Health Sciences and Nutrition]] warned that Mexico was particularly vulnerable to the COVID-19 pandemic because of underlying chronic illnesses such as [[obesity]], [[diabetes]], and [[hypertension]].<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/25/mexico-es-mas-vulnerable-al-coronavirus-por-prevalencia-de-enfermedades-cronicas-dijeron-especialistas/ |title= M\u00e9xico es m\u00e1s vulnerable al coronavirus por prevalencia de enfermedades cr\u00f3nicas, dijeron especialistas |author=  |language=es |date= March 25, 2020 |website= Infobae}}</ref> Also on 25 March President L\u00f3pez Obrador ordered the [[Mexican Air Force]] to rescue Mexicans trapped in [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Argentina|Argentina]].<ref name=airforce>[https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/25/lopez-obrador-ordeno-a-la-fuera-aerea-trasladar-a-su-pais-a-argentinos-varados-en-mexico-por-el-coronavirus-y-repatriar-a-connacionales/ L\u00f3pez Obrador orden\u00f3 a la Fuerza A\u00e9rea una misi\u00f3n de rescate de mexicanos y argentinos varados por coronavirus]{{in lang|es}} Infobae, 25 Mar 2020</ref> In Baja California, [[PROFECO]] closed two businesses in Tijuana for price-gouging.<ref name=profecobc>{{cite web |url= http://www.hiptex.com.mx/noticias/15232/clausura-profeco-dos-comercios-por-subir-precios-de-productos-basicos |title= Clausura Profeco dos comercios por subir precios de productos b\u00e1sicos |author=  |language=es |date= March 25, 2020 |website= Hiptex}}</ref> In Mexico City, Head of Government [[Claudia Sheinbaum]] announced financial support for families and micro industries affected by the pandemic. She also announced that automobile verification would be suspended through April 19. Movie theaters, bars, nightclubs, gyms, and other entertainment centers will remain closed.<ref name=finsupport>{{cite web |url= https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/25/creditos-para-micronegocios-y-500-pesos-para-ninos-las-acciones-de-cdmx-para-apoyar-a-la-poblacion-durante-emergencia-por-coronavirus/ |title= Cr\u00e9ditos para micronegocios y 500 pesos para ni\u00f1os: las acciones de CDMX para apoyar a la poblaci\u00f3n durante emergencia por coronavirus |author=  |language=es |date= March 25, 2020 |website= Infobae}}</ref> The same day it was reported that one man died from COVID-19 in [[San Luis Potos\u00ed]], raising the total to 6 reported deaths in Mexico and 475 confirmed cases.<ref name=\"death6\">{{cite web|author= Roc\u00edo L\u00f3pez |title= Muere hombre en San Luis Potos\u00ed por COVID-19; van 6 en M\u00e9xico|url= https://www.milenio.com/estados/coronavirus-san-luis-potosi-reportan-muerto-covid-19 |website=Milenio|date=March 25, 2020|language=es}}</ref><ref name=\"25march\">{{cite web|author= Redacci\u00f3n Digital |title= Van 6 muertes en M\u00e9xico por COVID-19; casos positivos ascienden a 475 |url= https://heraldodemexico.com.mx/pais/coronavirus-mexico-muertes-covid19-casos-positivos-contagios-hoy-miercoles-25-marzo-2020-fase-dos-secretaria-salud/ |website=El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico|date=March 25, 2020|language=es}}</ref> Governor [[Miguel Barbosa Huerta]] ([[National Regeneration Movement|Morena]]) claimed that only the wealthy were at risk, since the poor are immune to COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/26/americas/mexico-coronavirus-luis-miguel-barbosa-intl/index.html |title= Mexican governor claims poor people are 'immune' from coronavirus |author1= Matt Rivers|author2= Natalie Gall\u00f3n |author3= CNN|language=en |date= March 26, 2020 |website= CNN}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March, President L\u00f3pez Obrador revealed he asked the [[G20]] to ensure that wealthy countries cannot take control of the world's medical supplies. He also called for assurances that borders would not be closed to commerce and that [[tariff]]s would not be unilaterally increased. Lastly, he called for an end to racism and discrimination.<ref name=g20>{{cite web |url= https://www.tvazteca.com/aztecanoticias/politica/notas/pide-amlo-en-g-20-que-onu-controle-comercio-de-medicamentos-de-covid-19 |title= Pide AMLO en G-20 que ONU controle comercio de medicamentos de COVID-19 |author= |language=es |date= March 26, 2020 |website= TV Azteca}}</ref> The Mexican government announced it would suspend most sectors' activities starting 26 March until 19 April, with the exception of health and energy sectors, the oil industry; and public services such as water supply, waste management and public safety.<ref name=suspend_govt>{{cite news|last=Rueda |first=Rivelino|title=A partir de hoy para gobierno actividades|url=https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/nacional/a-partir-de-hoy-para-gobierno-actividades|work=El Financiero|date=March 26, 2020|access-date=March 26, 2020|language=es}}</ref> Protesters in [[Sonora]] insisted that the government limit border crossings with the United States.<ref name=border>{{cite web |url= https://news.yahoo.com/mexicans-demand-crackdown-americans-crossing-154146270.html |title= Coronavirus: Mexicans demand crackdown on Americans crossing the border |author= BBC |language=en |date= March 26, 2020 |website= Yahoo! News}}</ref> [[Chihuahua (state)|Chihuahua]] announced that \u201cin the next few days\u201d it will start to quarantine migrants who are returned to the [[Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez]] border crossing. About 65 migrants are deported from [[El Paso, Texas]] daily, about 5,200 this year.<ref name=chi>{{cite web |url= https://apnews.com/cf7b480e9e1dc84d1970665120302d9e |title= Mexican border city to quarantine returning migrants |author= |language=en |date= March 26, 2020 |website= AP}}</ref> Two more deaths were reported on this day; 585 cases were confirmed, and there were 2,156 suspected cases.<ref name=\"26march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.radioformula.com.mx/noticias/mexico/20200326/585-casos-coronavirus-en-mexico-salud-federal-hoy-ultimas-noticias-26-de-marzo/amp/ | title= Ya hay 585 casos confirmados de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico |author=Diego Santiago|work=Grupo F\u00f3rmula|date= March 26, 2020}}</ref> [[Human Rights Watch]] accused AMLO of endangering lives by not providing accurate information about the pandemic.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.hrw.org/news/2020/03/26/mexico-mexicans-need-accurate-covid-19-information |title= Mexico: Mexicans Need Accurate COVID-19 Information |author= |language=en |date= March 26, 2020 |website= Human Rights Watch}}</ref> The government of San Luis Potosi reported the death of a 57-year-old man on March 26, bringing the total number of deaths in the country to nine. He had hypertension and diabetes.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://mexico.as.com/mexico/2020/03/27/tikitakas/1585280194_313276.html  |title= Coronavirus: San Luis confirma la segunda muerte en el estado |author= |language=es |date= March 26, 2020 |website= Mexico AS}}</ref> Citizens of [[Nogales, Sonora]] block border crossing from [[Nogales, Arizona]] in order to prevent the entrance of individuals with the virus infection and to prevent shortages of food, bottled water, toilet paper and cleaning supplies in local stores.<ref name=nogales>{{cite web |url= https://www.univision.com/noticias/america-latina/el-mundo-al-reves-mexicanos-bloquean-frontera-para-que-no-entren-a-su-pais-estadounidenses-contagiados-por-el-covid-19 |title= Mexicanos bloquean frontera para que no entren a su pa\u00eds estadounidenses contagiados por el COVID-19 |author= Isaias Alvarado |language=es |date= March 26, 2020 |website= Univision Noticias}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the Secretary of Health, a plurality of the 585 people infected in Mexico, 70, are between 30 and 34 years old. People over 65 are second, followed by those 25 to 29 and 45 to 49. The states with the most incidents are Mexico City (83), Jalisco (64) and Nuevo Leon (57).<ref>{{cite web |url= https://mexico.as.com/mexico/2020/03/27/tikitakas/1585334510_686136.html |title= De 30 a 34, la media de edad de contagios por coronavirus COVID-19 en M\u00e9xico |author= |language=es |date= March 27, 2020 |website= Mexico AS}}</ref>\n\nOn March 27 the federal government bought 5,000 ventilators from China as the government prepares for Phase 3 of the pandemic.<ref name=ventilator /> The total confirmed cases rose to 717; twelve deaths were reported, and there were 2,475 suspected cases.<ref name=\"27march\">{{cite web|url= https://politico.mx/minuta-politica/minuta-politica-gobierno-federal/ssa-presentar%C3%A1-informe-diario-sobre-coronavirus-en-m%C3%A9xico/ | title= Ssa: 717 casos confirmados de coronavirus y 2 mil 475 sospechosos |language=es |author=Pol\u00edtico MX|work=Pol\u00edtico.mx|date= March 27, 2020}}</ref> [[PROFECO]] (Office of the Federal Prosecutor for the Consumer) said it will fine merchants who unfairly raise the prices on household goods.<ref name=fine>{{cite web |url= https://www.adn40.mx/noticia/mexico/notas/2020-03-27-08-26/multa-de-hasta-3-millones-a-quien-suba-el-precio-de-la-canasta-basica |title= Multa de hasta 3 millones a quien suba el precio de la canasta b\u00e1sica |author= Redacci\u00f3n ADN40|language=es |date= March 27, 2020 |website= ADN40}}</ref> The governors of [[Governor of Nuevo Le\u00f3n|Nuevo Le\u00f3n]], [[Governor of Tamaulipas|Tamaulipas]] and [[Governor of Coahuila|Coahuila]] asked the federal government to close the border with [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|the United States]].<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.sinembargo.mx/27-03-2020/3756883 |title= Gobiernos de Coahuila, Nuevo Le\u00f3n y Tamaulipas piden a AMLO cerrar la frontera con EU por COVID-19 |author= Redacci\u00f3n/ Sin Embargo|language=es |date= March 27, 2020 |website= Sin Embargo}}</ref> \n\nOn March 28, Governor [[Omar Fayad]] of [[Hidalgo (state)|Hidalgo]] announced in a tweet that he tested positive for the virus and said that he was in self-quarantine.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/salud/omar-fayad-gobernador-de-hidalgo-da-positivo-a-covid-19 | title= Omar Fayad, gobernador de Hidalgo, da positivo a COVID-19 |author=Redacci\u00f3n |work=El Financiero|language=es |date= March 28, 2020}}</ref> The [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Mexico]] said services should be held indoors with no more than twenty people present. They may cancel all [[Holy Week in Mexico|Holy Week]] celebrations if things do not improve.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.milenio.com/politica/arquidiocesis-celebracion-semana-santa-puerta-cerrada |title= Arquidi\u00f3cesis pide que celebraciones de Semana Santa sean a puerta cerrada |author= Elia Castillo|language=es |date= March 28, 2020 |website= Milenio}}</ref> In the evening the Secretariat of Health reported 131 new confirmed cases and four more deaths, raising the total to 848 confirmed cases and 16 deaths.<ref name=\"28march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/sube-a-848-los-contagiados-de-coronavirus-en-mexico/1372746 | title= Sube a 848 los contagiados de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico |author=Redacci\u00f3n |work=Exc\u00e9lsior|language=es|date= March 28, 2020}}</ref> Governor [[Cuauht\u00e9moc Blanco]] of Morelos announced the seventh case and first death due to COVID-19 in the state, a 37-year-old man who had recently traveled to the United States.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.milenio.com/estados/coronavirus-confirman-el-primer-muerto-en-morelos-por-covid-19 |title= Cuauht\u00e9moc Blanco confirma la primer muerte por COVID-19 en Morelos |author= |language=es |date= March 28, 2020 |website= Milenio}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.diariodemorelos.com/noticias/situaci-n-actual-del-coronavirus-covid-19-en-morelos?fbclid=IwAR2mfAxLsQlJ6o3tndIvL0n8fOLVDzTE0pSZewHYL9ReOGBi6UznpBcmv4Y |title= SITUACI\u00d3N ACTUAL DEL CORONAVIRUS COVID-19 EN MORELOS |author= |language=es |date= March 28, 2020 |website= Diario de Morelos}}</ref> San Luis Potosi suspended wakes and funerals; the dead should be taken directly from the hospital to the [[crematorium]].<ref name=funeral>{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/estados/coronavirus-suspenden-funerales-por-covid-19-en-san-luis-potosi |title= Suspenden funerales por COVID-19 en San Luis Potos\u00ed |author= Redacci\u00f3n El Universal |language=es |date= March 28, 2020 |website= El Universal}}</ref>\n\nTabasco Governor [[Ad\u00e1n Augusto L\u00f3pez Hern\u00e1ndez]] tested positive for COVID-19 on 29 March.<ref name=loppez_hernandez>{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/estados/coronavirus-gobernador-de-tabasco-da-positivo-covid-19-0 |title= Gobernador de Tabasco da positivo al Covid-19 |author=  |language=es |date= March 29, 2020 |website= El Universal}}</ref> Two tunnels with disinfectant spray were installed in the subways system of [[General Escobedo|Escobedo, Nuevo Le\u00f3n]].<ref>[https://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/por-covid-19-colocan-tuneles-para-desinfectar-hasta-30-personas-por-minuto/1372842 Por Covid-19, colocan t\u00faneles para desinfectar hasta 30 personas por minuto] {{in lang|es}} by Aracely Garza, Excelsior, 29 Mar 2020</ref> The government of [[Yucat\u00e1n]] threatens fines of $86,000 pesos and up to three years in prison for individuals who have tested positive for coronavirus and do not self-quarantine.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://noticieros.televisa.com/ultimas-noticias/coronavirus-multas-86-mil-pesos-personas-enfermas-aislen-yucatan/ |title= Multas de 86 mil pesos a personas con coronavirus que no se a\u00edslen en Yucat\u00e1n |author=  |language=es |date= March 29, 2020 |website= Noticieros Televisa}}</ref> The state of [[Quer\u00e9taro]] registered its first death from COVID-19, a 56-year-old man.<ref name=gov_tabasco>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/estados/coronavirus-queretaro-registra-la-primera-muerte-por-covid-19 Quer\u00e9taro registra la primera muerte por COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} El Universal, 29 March 2020</ref> The same day 993 cases of COVID-19 and 20 deaths from the disease were confirmed.<ref name=\"29march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.publimetro.com.mx/mx/coronavirus-covid-19/2020/03/29/casos-muertes-coronavirus-mexico-29-marzo-2020.html | title= Suman 993 casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; hay 20 muertos|author=Publimetro |work=Publimetro|language=es|date= March 29, 2020}}</ref> Between 27 and 29 March, 566 Mexicans were brought home from other countries: 62 from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Colombia|Colombia]], 53 from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Ecuador|Ecuador]], 299 from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Peru|Peru]], 28 from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Guatemala|Guatemala (via land)]], and 134 from [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Cuba|Cuba]]. In turn, the Mexican government helped 86 people return to Ecuador, 99 to Peru, and 49 to Cuba.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.jornada.com.mx/ultimas/politica/2020/03/29/en-dos-dias-fueron-repatriados-576-mexicanos-suman-mas-de-8-mil-8945.html |title= En dos d\u00edas, fueron repatriados 576 mexicanos; suman m\u00e1s de 8 mil |author=La Redacci\u00f3n  |language=es |date= March 29, 2020 |website= La Jornada}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, the total number of cases of COVID-19 surpassed one thousand with 1,094 confirmed cases and 28 reported deaths in the country. In the evening, a national health emergency was declared in Mexico by Secretary [[Marcelo Ebrard]]; all sectors in the country are urged to stop most of their activities.<ref name=\"30march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/sociedad/coronavirus-30-de-marzo-mexico-supera-los-mil-contagios-de-coronavirus-suman-mil-94 | title= M\u00c9XICO, EN EMERGENCIA SANITARIA; SUPERA LOS MIL CASOS DE CORONAVIRUS |author=Redacci\u00f3n  |work=El Universal|language=es|date= March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn the early morning of 31 March, 50,000 test kits, 100,000 masks and five ventilators (donated by [[Jack Ma]] and the [[Alibaba Group|Alibaba]] Foundation of China) arrived at the [[Mexico City International Airport]].<ref>{{cite web |url= https://aristeguinoticias.com/0104/mexico/llegan-a-mexico-50-mil-kits-de-pruebas-para-detectar-covid-19-donados-por-china/ |title= Llegan a M\u00e9xico 50 mil kits de pruebas para detectar Covid-19, donados por China |author= |language=es |date= March 31, 2020 |website= Aristegui Noticias}}</ref> Nurses in Jalisco have been forced to get off public transportation and physically attacked by people fearful of COVID-19. Medical workers there and elsewhere have been advised not to wear their uniforms outside the hospital.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/31/bajan-del-transporte-a-enfermeras-en-jalisco-y-les-rocian-cloro-por-miedo-a-contagios-de-covid-19/ |title= Bajan del transporte a enfermeras en Jalisco y les roc\u00edan cloro por miedo a contagios de Covid-19 |author= |language=es |date= March 31, 2020 |website= Infobae}}</ref> The same day the total confirmed cases of COVID-19 reached 1215 and one more death was reported. The government of [[Mexico City]] announced that 90% of the businesses in Mexico City would have to close because of the national health emergency declaration of the day before.<ref name=\"31march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-31-de-marzo-casos-de-covid-19-en-mexico-llegan-mil-215-hay-29-muertos | title= CASOS DE CORONAVIRUS EN M\u00c9XICO LLEGAN A MIL 215; HAY 29 MUERTOS |author=Redacci\u00f3n  |work=El Universal|language=es|date= March 31, 2020}}</ref> In [[Austin, Texas]], Public Health officials started investigating an apparent cluster of COVID-19 after 28 of 70 \u201cspring breakers\u201d (students at the [[University of Texas at Austin]]) tested positive following their trip to [[Cabo San Lucas]], [[Baja California Sur]] in early March.<ref>{{cite web|website=[[KXAN-TV]]|date=March 31, 2020|title=28 of 70 spring breakers on Mexico trip test positive for coronavirus |url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KXAN-TV}}</ref> The [[Mexican Social Security Institute|Mexican Social Security Institute (IMSS)]] in [[Monclova]], Coahuila, reported that 29 medical and nursing staff tested positive for COVID-19. No patients have been infected.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-mexico/coronavirus-infects-29-medical-workers-at-mexico-hospital-idUSKBN21J3W2 |title= Coronavirus infects 29 medical workers at Mexico hospital |author= |language=en |date= March 31, 2020 |website= Reuters}}</ref>\n\n=== April 2020 ===\n\n==== April 1 to 500{{Original research|date=April 2020}} ====\n[[File: Monterrey airport covid19.jpg |thumbnail|right|People wearing face masks at the [[Monterrey International Airport]] due to the COVID-19 pandemic.]]\nIt was reported on 1 April that seven migrants from Puebla residing in [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in New York (state)|New York]] have died of COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.animalpolitico.com/2020/04/siete-migrantes-poblanos-muertos-nueva-york-covid-19/ |title= Suman siete migrantes poblanos muertos en Nueva York por COVID-19 |author= |language=es |date= April 1, 2020 |website= Animal Pol\u00edtico}}</ref> Authorities reported 46% of cases as recoveries, which represents approximately 634 recoveries.<ref name=\"youtube1\"/> In Coahuila, 21  health workers contracted the virus and one doctor died from it, bringing the number of deaths among doctors employed by IMSS to four. Nineteen of the 21 cases in Coahuila are mild and the individuals are ambulatory.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/several-health-workers-have-contracted-covid-19-mexico |title= Several health workers have contracted COVID-19 in Mexico |author= |language=en |date= April 1, 2020 |website= El Universal English}}</ref> Later the same day, 1,378 cases and 37 deaths of COVID-19 were reported in Mexico.<ref name=\"1april\">{{cite web|url= https://heraldodemexico.com.mx/pais/coronavirus-covid-19-mexico-resumen-miercoles-1-abril-2020-secretaria-salud-muertos-contagiados-cifras/ | title= Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: Resumen mi\u00e9rcoles 1 de abril 2020 |author= Redacci\u00f3n Digital El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico |work=El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico|language=es|date= April 1, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn April 2, 1,510 cases of COVID-19 and 13 more deaths related to the disease were confirmed by Mexican authorities.<ref name=\"2april\">{{cite web|url= https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/nacional/llega-a-50-la-cifra-de-muertos-por-coronavirus-y-van-mil-510-casos-confirmados | title= Llega a 50 la cifra de muertos por coronavirus en M\u00e9xico y van mil 510 casos confirmados |author=Redacci\u00f3n  |work=El Financiero|language=es|date= April 2, 2020}}</ref> In Mexico City, as hotels are forced to close, hotel guests are evicted from their rooms.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/metropoli/cdmx/a-la-calle-hoteles-de-la-cdmx-desalojan-a-huespedes-ante-cuarentena-pandemia-covid-19-coronavirus-5052588.html |title= \u00a1A la calle! Hoteles de la CDMX desalojan a hu\u00e9spedes ante Covid-19 |author= Eduardo Torres |language=es |date= April 2, 2020 |website= El Sol de M\u00e9xico}}</ref>\n\nOn April 3, 1,688 cases and 60 deaths were confirmed by the Secretariat of Health.<ref name=\"3april\">{{cite web|url= https://politica.expansion.mx/mexico/2020/04/03/los-casos-positivos-de-coronavirus-se-elevan-a-1-688-y-a-60-los-decesos| title= Los casos positivos de coronavirus se elevan a 1,688 y a 60 los decesos|author=Expansi\u00f3n Pol\u00edtica  |work=Expansi\u00f3n Pol\u00edtica|language=es|date= April 3, 2020}}</ref> The following day, 202 more cases and 19 more deaths were confirmed by Mexican authorities.<ref name=\"4april\">{{cite web|url= https://www.dineroenimagen.com/actualidad/aumenta-1890-el-numero-de-contagiados-por-coronavirus-en-mexico/121274 | title= Aumenta a 1,890 el n\u00famero de contagiados por coronavirus en M\u00e9xico |author= |work=Dinero en Imagen |language=es|date= April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 April, President L\u00f3pez Obrador presented his plan to reactivate the economy. He said he did not want to increase fuel prices or taxes, and he was looking to hire more medical professionals for the armed forces. He said there was sufficient money to build the proposed thermoelectric plants that are needed in Yucat\u00e1n, Baja California and elsewhere. He stated that he had support from the private sector and he expressed his confidence that Mexico would soon overcome the current crisis.<ref name=plan>{{cite web|website=Mexico AS|title=AMLO presenta sus medidas para reactivar econom\u00eda ante el COVID-19 |language=es|trans-title=AMLO presents his measures to revive the economy effected by COVID-19|date=Apr 5, 2020 |author=Uriel Salmeron |url=https://mexico.as.com/mexico/2020/04/06/tikitakas/1586130668_050121.html}}</ref> On the same day , the total number of cases surpassed two thousand with 2143 cases and 94 deaths.<ref name=\"5april\">{{cite web|url= https://noticieros.televisa.com/ultimas-noticias/coronavirus-conferencia-mexico-hoy-5-abril-2020/ | title= Suman 94 muertos en M\u00e9xico por coronavirus; hay 2 mil 143 casos |author= Noticieros Televisa |work=Noticieros Televisa |language=es|date= April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\nPresident L\u00f3pez Obrador and Governor Blanco of Morelos dedicated the ISSSTE hospital \u201cCarlos Calero\u201d in Cuernavaca that was going to be set aside to care for patients with COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|website=Mexico AS|title=Cuauht\u00e9moc Blanco y AMLO pusieron ejemplo de la 'sana distancia' |language=es|trans-title=Cuauht\u00e9moc Blanco and AMLO set an example of \u2018social distancing\u2019|date=Apr 5, 2020 |author=Erick de la Rosa |url=https://mexico.as.com/mexico/2020/04/05/tikitakas/1586047733_148789.html}}</ref> Fifteen new deaths were registered on 5 April, bringing the total to 94. The age range of the deceased was from 26 to 91 years old with a median age of 56.5. Of the 94 dead, 79% were males and 21% were females.<ref>{{cite web |website=Mexico AS|title=Muertos por Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico hoy, 5 de abril|language=es|trans-title=Deaths by Coronavirus in Mexico today, April 5|date=Apr 5, 2020 |author=Juan Carlos Navarro |url=https://mexico.as.com/autor/juan_carlos_navarro_hernandez/a/}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 April, 2439 cases were confirmed and the total number of deaths surpassed one hundred with 125 deaths reported.<ref name=\"6april\">{{cite web|url= https://heraldodemexico.com.mx/pais/muertos-mexico-covid-19-casos-confirmados-coronavirus-corte-secretaria-salud-lunes-6-abril-2020/ | title= COVID-19 en M\u00e9xico: Ssa reporta 125 muertos y dos mil 439 casos confirmados |author= Redacci\u00f3n Digital El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico |work=El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico |language=es|date= April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe [[List of diplomatic missions of Mexico|Mexican Consulate]] in [[Shanghai]], China, announced on April 7 that the [[Aerom\u00e9xico]] ''Misionero de Paz,'' a [[Boeing 787 Dreamliner|Boeing 787-8]] filled with emergency medical supplies was en route to Mexico.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://mty.telediario.mx/nacional/avion-con-suministros-medicos-por-covid-19-se-dirige-mexico-desde-china |title= Avi\u00f3n con suministros m\u00e9dicos por covid-19 se dirige a M\u00e9xico desde China |author= Milenio Digital |date= April 7, 2020 |language=es |website= Telediario}}</ref> That same day, 2785 cases and 141 death related to COVID-19 were confirmed.<ref name=\"7april\" >{{cite web |url= https://heraldodemexico.com.mx/pais/coronavirus-covid-19-mexico-resumen-muertos-contagiados-secretaria-salud-martes-7-abril-2020/ |title= Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: Resumen martes 7 de abril 2020 |author= Redacci\u00f3n Digital El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico |date= April 7, 2020 |language=es |website= El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico}}</ref>\n\nOn April 8, twenty medical and nursing schools withdrew their students from social service in hospitals due to the lack of adequate protection.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.jornada.com.mx/ultimas/politica/2020/04/08/anuies-se-une-al-ipn-y-a-unam-y-retira-sus-estudiantes-de-hospitales-7806.html |title= Veintena de universidades tambi\u00e9n retira estudiantes de hospitales |author= Jos\u00e9 Antonio Rom\u00e1n |date= April 8, 2020 |language=es |website= La Jornada}}</ref> [[Hugo L\u00f3pez-Gatell Ram\u00edrez]], head of the Undersecretariat of Prevention and Health Promotion at the Mexican Secretariat of Health, estimated there were unconfirmed 26,519 cases of COVID-19 in the country.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/mexicos-health-ministry-estimates-there-are-26000-covid-19-cases-country |title= Mexico's Health Ministry estimates there are 26,000 COVID-19 cases in the country|author= Teresa Moreno |date= April 8, 2020 |language=en |website= El Universal}}</ref> In the evening it was announced that Mexico surpassed the three thousand confirmed cases with 3,181 cases and 174 deaths.<ref name=\"8april\">{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-8-de-abril-mexico-ya-supera-los-3-mil-contagios-de-covid-19-contabiliza-174 |title= M\u00c9XICO YA SUPERA LOS 3 MIL CONTAGIOS DE CORONAVIRUS; CONTABILIZA 174 MUERTOS |author= Redacci\u00f3n |date= April 8, 2020 |language=es |website= El Universal}}</ref> The following day, 260 more cases and 20 more death were reported by Mexican authorities.<ref name=\"9april\">{{cite web |url= https://heraldodemexico.com.mx/pais/muertos-mexico-covid19-casos-confirmados-coronavirus-reporte-secretaria-de-salud-jueves-9-abril-2020/ |title= COVID-19 M\u00e9xico: SSa reporta 194 muertos y tres mil 441 casos confirmados |author= Redacci\u00f3n Digital El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico |date= April 9, 2020 |language=es |website= El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico}}</ref>\n\nOn April 10, the total confirmed deaths surpassed two hundred with 233 deaths and 3,844 cases confirmed by Mexican authorities.<ref name=\"10april\">{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-10-de-abril-mexico-supera-los-200-muertos-por-covid-19-llega-3-mil-844-contagios |title= M\u00c9XICO SUPERA LOS 200 MUERTOS POR COVID-19; LLEGA A 3 MIL 844 CONTAGIOS |author= Redacci\u00f3n |date= April 10, 2020 |language=es |website= El Universal}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n\n=== [[Secretariat of Health (Mexico)|SALUD]] reported Mexico totals ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"display: inline-table; font-size:90%; text-align:right;\"\n|+ <big> As of April 11</big>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\"  style=\"text-align:left; width:140px;\"|State\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| Cases\n! Deaths\n! Recoveries\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:right; padding-right:18px;\" scope=\"row\" | 4219\n! style=\"text-align:right; padding-right:18px;\" scope=\"row\" | 273\n! style=\"text-align:right; padding-right:18px;\" scope=\"row\" | 634\n|-\n!style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Mexico City}}\n||1117||49||196\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|State of Mexico}}\n||498||19||102\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Baja California}}\n||278||20||31\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Puebla}}\n||243||18||46\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Sinaloa}}\n||214||24||12\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Quintana Roo}}\n||216||18||38\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Coahuila}}\n||156||11||38\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Jalisco}}\n||150||11||87\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Tabasco}}\n||143||12||36\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Nuevo Le\u00f3n}}\n||119||5||66\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Yucat\u00e1n}}\n||103||4||5\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Baja California Sur}}\n||102||2||6\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Guanajuato}}\n||81||5||26\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:left\" |{{Flag2|Veracruz}}\n||