The Sinbad Show]]''\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Ya}}\n| Himself\n| Episode: The Mr. Science Show\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[The Bernie Mac Show]]''\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Ya}}\n| Himself\n| Episode: Goodbye Dolly\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" | 2005\n| ''[[Barbershop (TV series)|BarberShop: The Series]]''\n| {{Ya}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| \n| \n|-\n| ''[[WrestleMania 21]]''\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Ya}}\n| Himself\n| \n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Black. White.]]''\n| {{Ya}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| \n| \n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Friday: The Animated Series]]''\n| {{Ya}}\n| {{Ya}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| \n| \n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[30 for 30]]''\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Ya}}\n| {{Na}}\n| \n| Episode: [[Straight Outta L.A.]]\n|-\n| 2010\u20132013\n| ''[[Are We There Yet? (TV series)|Are We There Yet?]]''\n| {{Ya}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Ya}}\n| Terrence Kingston\n| Recurring Role; 20 Episodes\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Amazon Studios#2nd pilot season (February 6, 2014)|The Rebels]]''\n| {{Ya}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| \n| Pilot of unproduced series\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[The Defiant Ones (documentary)|The Defiant Ones]]''\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Na}}\n| {{Ya}}\n| Himself\n| Documentary\n|}\n\n===Video games===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-  style=\"background:#b0c4de; text-align:center;\"\n! Title || Year || Role || Other notes || {{Abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n| ''[[Call of Duty: Black Ops]]'' || 2010 || Chief Petty Officer Joseph Bowman/[[Military Assistance Command, Vietnam \u2013 Studies and Observations Group|SOG]] multiplayer announcer || Voice and likeness actor || <ref>{{cite news |url=https://n4g.com/news/635528/ice-cubes-voice-in-black-ops |title=Ice Cube's Voice in Black Ops |date=29 October 2010 |access-date=4 November 2018 |work=N4G}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://kotaku.com/5675404/ice-cube-adding-call-of-duty-to-his-resume |title=Ice Cube Adding Call Of Duty To His Resume |first=\nBrian |last=Ashcraft |date=28 October 2010 |access-date=4 November 